119// Helper class to iterate WAL logs in a directory in chronological order.
120class WALFileIterator {
121 public:
122 explicit WALFileIterator(const std::string& parent_dir,
123 const std::vector<std::string>& filenames);
124 // REQUIRES Valid() == true
125 std::string GetNextWAL();
126 bool Valid() const { return wal_file_iter_ != log_files_.end(); }
127
128 private:
129 // WAL log file names(s)
130 std::string parent_dir_;
131 std::vector<std::string> log_files_;
132 std::vector<std::string>::const_iterator wal_file_iter_;
133};
134
135WALFileIterator::WALFileIterator(const std::string& parent_dir,
136 const std::vector<std::string>& filenames)
137 : parent_dir_(parent_dir) {
138 // populate wal logs
139 assert(!filenames.empty());
140 for (const auto& fname : filenames) {
141 uint64_t file_num = 0;
142 FileType file_type;
143 bool parse_ok = ParseFileName(fname, &file_num, &file_type);
144 if (parse_ok && file_type == kWalFile) {
145 log_files_.push_back(fname);
146 }
147 }
148
149 std::sort(log_files_.begin(), log_files_.end(),
150 [](const std::string& lhs, const std::string& rhs) {
151 uint64_t num1 = 0;
152 uint64_t num2 = 0;
153 FileType type1;
154 FileType type2;
155 bool parse_ok1 = ParseFileName(lhs, &num1, &type1);
156 bool parse_ok2 = ParseFileName(rhs, &num2, &type2);
157#ifndef NDEBUG
158 assert(parse_ok1);
159 assert(parse_ok2);
160#else
161 (void)parse_ok1;
162 (void)parse_ok2;
163#endif
164 return num1 < num2;
165 });
166 wal_file_iter_ = log_files_.begin();
167}
168
169std::string WALFileIterator::GetNextWAL() {
170 assert(Valid());
171 std::string ret;
172 if (wal_file_iter_ != log_files_.end()) {
173 ret.assign(parent_dir_);
174 if (ret.back() != kFilePathSeparator) {
175 ret.push_back(kFilePathSeparator);
176 }
177 ret.append(*wal_file_iter_);
178 ++wal_file_iter_;
179 }
180 return ret;
181}

208LDBCommand* LDBCommand::InitFromCmdLineArgs(
209 int argc, char const* const* argv, const Options& options,
210 const LDBOptions& ldb_options,
211 const std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor>* column_families) {
212 std::vector<std::string> args;
213 for (int i = 1; i < argc; i++) {
214 args.emplace_back(argv[i]);
215 }
216 return InitFromCmdLineArgs(args, options, ldb_options, column_families,
217 SelectCommand);
218}

220void LDBCommand::ParseSingleParam(const std::string& param,
221 ParsedParams& parsed_params,
222 std::vector<std::string>& cmd_tokens) {
223 const std::string OPTION_PREFIX = "--";
224
225 if (param[0] == '-' && param[1] == '-') {
226 std::vector<std::string> splits = StringSplit(param, '=');
227 // --option_name=option_value
228 if (splits.size() == 2) {
229 std::string optionKey = splits[0].substr(OPTION_PREFIX.size());
230 parsed_params.option_map[optionKey] = splits[1];
231 } else if (splits.size() == 1) {
232 // --flag_name
233 std::string optionKey = splits[0].substr(OPTION_PREFIX.size());
234 parsed_params.flags.push_back(optionKey);
235 } else {
236 // --option_name=option_value, option_value contains '='
237 std::string optionKey = splits[0].substr(OPTION_PREFIX.size());
238 parsed_params.option_map[optionKey] =
239 param.substr(splits[0].length() + 1);
240 }
241 } else {
242 cmd_tokens.push_back(param);
243 }
244}
245
256LDBCommand* LDBCommand::InitFromCmdLineArgs(
257 const std::vector<std::string>& args, const Options& options,
258 const LDBOptions& ldb_options,
259 const std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor>* column_families,
260 const std::function<LDBCommand*(const ParsedParams&)>& selector) {
261 // --x=y command line arguments are added as x->y map entries in
262 // parsed_params.option_map.
263 //
264 // Command-line arguments of the form --hex end up in this array as hex to
265 // parsed_params.flags
266 ParsedParams parsed_params;
267
268 // Everything other than option_map and flags. Represents commands
269 // and their parameters. For eg: put key1 value1 go into this vector.
270 std::vector<std::string> cmdTokens;
271
272 for (const auto& arg : args) {
273 ParseSingleParam(arg, parsed_params, cmdTokens);
274 }
275
276 if (cmdTokens.size() < 1) {
277 fprintf(stderr, "Command not specified!");
278 return nullptr;
279 }
280
281 parsed_params.cmd = cmdTokens[0];
282 parsed_params.cmd_params.assign(cmdTokens.begin() + 1, cmdTokens.end());
283
284 LDBCommand* command = selector(parsed_params);
285
286 if (command) {
287 command->SetDBOptions(options);
288 command->SetLDBOptions(ldb_options);
289 command->SetColumnFamilies(column_families);
290 }
291 return command;
292}

432/* Run the command, and return the execute result. */
433void LDBCommand::Run() {
434 if (!exec_state_.IsNotStarted()) {
435 return;
436 }
437
438 if (!options_.env || options_.env == Env::Default()) {
439 Env* env = Env::Default();
440 Status s = Env::CreateFromUri(config_options_, env_uri_, fs_uri_, &env,
441 &env_guard_);
442 if (!s.ok()) {
443 fprintf(stderr, "%s\n", s.ToString().c_str());
444 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(s.ToString());
445 return;
446 }
447 options_.env = env;
448 }
449
450 if (db_ == nullptr && !NoDBOpen()) {
451 OpenDB();
452 if (exec_state_.IsFailed() && try_load_options_) {
453 // We don't always return if there is a failure because a WAL file or
454 // manifest file can be given to "dump" command so we should continue.
455 // --try_load_options is not valid in those cases.
456 return;
457 }
458 }
459
460 // We'll intentionally proceed even if the DB can't be opened because users
461 // can also specify a filename, not just a directory.
462 DoCommand();
463
464 if (exec_state_.IsNotStarted()) {
465 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Succeed("");
466 }
467
468 if (db_ != nullptr) {
469 CloseDB();
470 }
471}
472
473LDBCommand::LDBCommand(const std::map<std::string, std::string>& options,
474 const std::vector<std::string>& flags, bool is_read_only,
475 const std::vector<std::string>& valid_cmd_line_options)
476 : db_(nullptr),
477 db_ttl_(nullptr),
478 is_read_only_(is_read_only),
479 is_key_hex_(false),
480 is_value_hex_(false),
481 is_db_ttl_(false),
482 timestamp_(false),
483 try_load_options_(false),
484 create_if_missing_(false),
485 option_map_(options),
486 flags_(flags),
487 valid_cmd_line_options_(valid_cmd_line_options) {
488 auto itr = options.find(ARG_DB);
489 if (itr != options.end()) {
490 db_path_ = itr->second;
491 }
492
493 itr = options.find(ARG_ENV_URI);
494 if (itr != options.end()) {
495 env_uri_ = itr->second;
496 }
497
498 itr = options.find(ARG_FS_URI);
499 if (itr != options.end()) {
500 fs_uri_ = itr->second;
501 }
502
503 itr = options.find(ARG_CF_NAME);
504 if (itr != options.end()) {
505 column_family_name_ = itr->second;
506 } else {
507 column_family_name_ = kDefaultColumnFamilyName;
508 }
509
510 itr = options.find(ARG_SECONDARY_PATH);
511 secondary_path_ = "";
512 if (itr != options.end()) {
513 secondary_path_ = itr->second;
514 }
515
516 itr = options.find(ARG_LEADER_PATH);
517 leader_path_ = "";
518 if (itr != options.end()) {
519 leader_path_ = itr->second;
520 }
521
522 is_key_hex_ = IsKeyHex(options, flags);
523 is_value_hex_ = IsValueHex(options, flags);
524 is_db_ttl_ = IsFlagPresent(flags, ARG_TTL);
525 timestamp_ = IsFlagPresent(flags, ARG_TIMESTAMP);
526 try_load_options_ = IsTryLoadOptions(options, flags);
527 force_consistency_checks_ =
528 !IsFlagPresent(flags, ARG_DISABLE_CONSISTENCY_CHECKS);
529 enable_blob_files_ = IsFlagPresent(flags, ARG_ENABLE_BLOB_FILES);
530 enable_blob_garbage_collection_ =
531 IsFlagPresent(flags, ARG_ENABLE_BLOB_GARBAGE_COLLECTION);
532 config_options_.ignore_unknown_options =
533 IsFlagPresent(flags, ARG_IGNORE_UNKNOWN_OPTIONS);
534}
535
536void LDBCommand::OpenDB() {
537 PrepareOptions();
538 if (!exec_state_.IsNotStarted()) {
539 return;
540 }
541 if (column_families_.empty() && !options_.merge_operator) {
542 // No harm to add a general merge operator if it is not specified.
543 options_.merge_operator = MergeOperators::CreateStringAppendOperator(':');
544 }
545 // Open the DB.
546 Status st;
547 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> handles_opened;
548 if (is_db_ttl_) {
549 // ldb doesn't yet support TTL DB with multiple column families
550 if (!column_family_name_.empty() || !column_families_.empty()) {
551 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
552 "ldb doesn't support TTL DB with multiple column families");
553 }
554 if (!secondary_path_.empty() || !leader_path_.empty()) {
555 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
556 "Open as secondary or follower is not supported for TTL DB yet.");
557 }
558 if (is_read_only_) {
559 st = DBWithTTL::Open(options_, db_path_, &db_ttl_, 0, true);
560 } else {
561 st = DBWithTTL::Open(options_, db_path_, &db_ttl_);
562 }
563 db_ = db_ttl_;
564 } else {
565 if (!secondary_path_.empty() && !leader_path_.empty()) {
566 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
567 "Cannot provide both secondary and leader paths");
568 }
569 if (is_read_only_ && secondary_path_.empty() && leader_path_.empty()) {
570 if (column_families_.empty()) {
571 st = DB::OpenForReadOnly(options_, db_path_, &db_);
572 } else {
573 st = DB::OpenForReadOnly(options_, db_path_, column_families_,
574 &handles_opened, &db_);
575 }
576 } else {
577 if (column_families_.empty()) {
578 if (secondary_path_.empty() && leader_path_.empty()) {
579 st = DB::Open(options_, db_path_, &db_);
580 } else if (!secondary_path_.empty()) {
581 st = DB::OpenAsSecondary(options_, db_path_, secondary_path_, &db_);
582 } else {
583 std::unique_ptr<DB> dbptr;
584 st = DB::OpenAsFollower(options_, db_path_, leader_path_, &dbptr);
585 db_ = dbptr.release();
586 }
587 } else {
588 if (secondary_path_.empty() && leader_path_.empty()) {
589 st = DB::Open(options_, db_path_, column_families_, &handles_opened,
590 &db_);
591 } else if (!secondary_path_.empty()) {
592 st = DB::OpenAsSecondary(options_, db_path_, secondary_path_,
593 column_families_, &handles_opened, &db_);
594 } else {
595 std::unique_ptr<DB> dbptr;
596 st = DB::OpenAsFollower(options_, db_path_, leader_path_,
597 column_families_, &handles_opened, &dbptr);
598 db_ = dbptr.release();
599 }
600 }
601 }
602 }
603 if (!st.ok()) {
604 std::string msg = st.ToString();
605 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(msg);
606 } else if (!handles_opened.empty()) {
607 assert(handles_opened.size() == column_families_.size());
608 bool found_cf_name = false;
609 for (size_t i = 0; i < handles_opened.size(); i++) {
610 cf_handles_[column_families_[i].name] = handles_opened[i];
611 ucmps_[handles_opened[i]->GetID()] = handles_opened[i]->GetComparator();
612 if (column_family_name_ == column_families_[i].name) {
613 found_cf_name = true;
614 }
615 }
616 if (!found_cf_name) {
617 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
618 "Non-existing column family " + column_family_name_);
619 CloseDB();
620 }
621 ColumnFamilyHandle* default_cf = db_->DefaultColumnFamily();
622 ucmps_[default_cf->GetID()] = default_cf->GetComparator();
623 } else {
624 // We successfully opened DB in single column family mode.
625 assert(column_families_.empty());
626 if (column_family_name_ != kDefaultColumnFamilyName) {
627 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
628 "Non-existing column family " + column_family_name_);
629 CloseDB();
630 }
631 ColumnFamilyHandle* default_cf = db_->DefaultColumnFamily();
632 ucmps_[default_cf->GetID()] = default_cf->GetComparator();
633 }
634}
635
636void LDBCommand::CloseDB() {
637 if (db_ != nullptr) {
638 for (auto& pair : cf_handles_) {
639 delete pair.second;
640 }
641 Status s = db_->Close();
642 s.PermitUncheckedError();
643 delete db_;
644 db_ = nullptr;
645 }
646}
647
648ColumnFamilyHandle* LDBCommand::GetCfHandle() {
649 if (!cf_handles_.empty()) {
650 auto it = cf_handles_.find(column_family_name_);
651 if (it == cf_handles_.end()) {
652 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
653 "Cannot find column family " + column_family_name_);
654 } else {
655 return it->second;
656 }
657 }
658 return db_->DefaultColumnFamily();
659}

701bool LDBCommand::ParseDoubleOption(
702 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& /*options*/,
703 const std::string& option, double& value,
704 LDBCommandExecuteResult& exec_state) {
705 auto itr = option_map_.find(option);
706 if (itr != option_map_.end()) {
707#if defined(CYGWIN)
708 char* str_end = nullptr;
709 value = std::strtod(itr->second.c_str(), &str_end);
710 if (str_end == itr->second.c_str()) {
711 exec_state =
712 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(option + " has an invalid value.");
713 } else if (errno == ERANGE) {
714 exec_state = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
715 option + " has a value out-of-range.");
716 } else {
717 return true;
718 }
719#else
720 try {
721 value = std::stod(itr->second);
722 return true;
723 } catch (const std::invalid_argument&) {
724 exec_state =
725 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(option + " has an invalid value.");
726 } catch (const std::out_of_range&) {
727 exec_state = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
728 option + " has a value out-of-range.");
729 }
730#endif
731 }
732 return false;
733}
734
742bool LDBCommand::ParseIntOption(
743 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& /*options*/,
744 const std::string& option, int& value,
745 LDBCommandExecuteResult& exec_state) {
746 auto itr = option_map_.find(option);
747 if (itr != option_map_.end()) {
748#if defined(CYGWIN)
749 char* str_end = nullptr;
750 value = strtol(itr->second.c_str(), &str_end, 10);
751 if (str_end == itr->second.c_str()) {
752 exec_state =
753 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(option + " has an invalid value.");
754 } else if (errno == ERANGE) {
755 exec_state = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
756 option + " has a value out-of-range.");
757 } else {
758 return true;
759 }
760#else
761 try {
762 value = std::stoi(itr->second);
763 return true;
764 } catch (const std::invalid_argument&) {
765 exec_state =
766 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(option + " has an invalid value.");
767 } catch (const std::out_of_range&) {
768 exec_state = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
769 option + " has a value out-of-range.");
770 }
771#endif
772 }
773 return false;
774}

781bool LDBCommand::ParseStringOption(
782 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& /*options*/,
783 const std::string& option, std::string* value) {
784 auto itr = option_map_.find(option);
785 if (itr != option_map_.end()) {
786 *value = itr->second;
787 return true;
788 }
789 return false;

791
797bool LDBCommand::ParseCompressionTypeOption(
798 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& /*options*/,
799 const std::string& option, CompressionType& value,
800 LDBCommandExecuteResult& exec_state) {
801 auto itr = option_map_.find(option);
802 if (itr != option_map_.end()) {
803 const std::string& comp = itr->second;
804 if (comp == "no") {
805 value = kNoCompression;
806 return true;
807 } else if (comp == "snappy") {
808 value = kSnappyCompression;
809 return true;
810 } else if (comp == "zlib") {
811 value = kZlibCompression;
812 return true;
813 } else if (comp == "bzip2") {
814 value = kBZip2Compression;
815 return true;
816 } else if (comp == "lz4") {
817 value = kLZ4Compression;
818 return true;
819 } else if (comp == "lz4hc") {
820 value = kLZ4HCCompression;
821 return true;
822 } else if (comp == "xpress") {
823 value = kXpressCompression;
824 return true;
825 } else if (comp == "zstd") {
826 value = kZSTD;
827 return true;
828 } else {
829 // Unknown compression.
830 exec_state = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
831 "Unknown compression algorithm: " + comp);
832 }
833 }
834 return false;
835}
836
837Status LDBCommand::MaybePopulateReadTimestamp(ColumnFamilyHandle* cfh,
838 ReadOptions& ropts,
839 Slice* read_timestamp) {
840 const size_t ts_sz = cfh->GetComparator()->timestamp_size();
841
842 auto iter = option_map_.find(ARG_READ_TIMESTAMP);
843 if (iter == option_map_.end()) {
844 if (ts_sz == 0) {
845 return Status::OK();
846 }
847 return Status::InvalidArgument(
848 "column family enables user-defined timestamp while --read_timestamp "
849 "is not provided.");
850 }
851 if (iter->second.empty()) {
852 if (ts_sz == 0) {
853 return Status::OK();
854 }
855 return Status::InvalidArgument(
856 "column family enables user-defined timestamp while --read_timestamp "
857 "is empty.");
858 }
859 if (ts_sz == 0) {
860 return Status::InvalidArgument(
861 "column family does not enable user-defined timestamps while "
862 "--read_timestamp is provided.");
863 }
864 Status s = EncodeUserProvidedTimestamp(iter->second, &read_timestamp_);
865 if (!s.ok()) {
866 return s;
867 }
868 *read_timestamp = read_timestamp_;
869 ropts.timestamp = read_timestamp;
870 return Status::OK();
871}

873void LDBCommand::OverrideBaseOptions() {
874 options_.create_if_missing = false;
875
876 int db_write_buffer_size;
877 if (ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_DB_WRITE_BUFFER_SIZE,
878 db_write_buffer_size, exec_state_)) {
879 if (db_write_buffer_size >= 0) {
880 options_.db_write_buffer_size = db_write_buffer_size;
881 } else {
882 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(ARG_DB_WRITE_BUFFER_SIZE +
883 " must be >= 0.");
884 }
885 }
886
887 if (options_.db_paths.size() == 0) {
888 options_.db_paths.emplace_back(db_path_,
889 std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max());
890 }
891
892 OverrideBaseCFOptions(static_cast<ColumnFamilyOptions*>(&options_));
893}
894
895void LDBCommand::OverrideBaseCFOptions(ColumnFamilyOptions* cf_opts) {
896 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
897 bool use_table_options = false;
898 int bits;
899 if (ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_BLOOM_BITS, bits, exec_state_)) {
900 if (bits > 0) {
901 use_table_options = true;
902 table_options.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(bits));
903 } else {
904 exec_state_ =
905 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(ARG_BLOOM_BITS + " must be > 0.");
906 }
907 }
908
909 int block_size;
910 if (ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_BLOCK_SIZE, block_size, exec_state_)) {
911 if (block_size > 0) {
912 use_table_options = true;
913 table_options.block_size = block_size;
914 } else {
915 exec_state_ =
916 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(ARG_BLOCK_SIZE + " must be > 0.");
917 }
918 }
919
920 // Default comparator is BytewiseComparator, so only when it's not, it
921 // means user has a command line override.
922 if (options_.comparator != nullptr &&
923 options_.comparator != BytewiseComparator()) {
924 cf_opts->comparator = options_.comparator;
925 }
926
927 cf_opts->force_consistency_checks = force_consistency_checks_;
928 if (use_table_options) {
929 cf_opts->table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
930 }
931
932 cf_opts->enable_blob_files = enable_blob_files_;
933
934 int min_blob_size;
935 if (ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_MIN_BLOB_SIZE, min_blob_size,
936 exec_state_)) {
937 if (min_blob_size >= 0) {
938 cf_opts->min_blob_size = min_blob_size;
939 } else {
940 exec_state_ =
941 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(ARG_MIN_BLOB_SIZE + " must be >= 0.");
942 }
943 }
944
945 int blob_file_size;
946 if (ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_BLOB_FILE_SIZE, blob_file_size,
947 exec_state_)) {
948 if (blob_file_size > 0) {
949 cf_opts->blob_file_size = blob_file_size;
950 } else {
951 exec_state_ =
952 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(ARG_BLOB_FILE_SIZE + " must be > 0.");
953 }
954 }
955
956 cf_opts->enable_blob_garbage_collection = enable_blob_garbage_collection_;
957
958 double blob_garbage_collection_age_cutoff;
959 if (ParseDoubleOption(option_map_, ARG_BLOB_GARBAGE_COLLECTION_AGE_CUTOFF,
960 blob_garbage_collection_age_cutoff, exec_state_)) {
961 if (blob_garbage_collection_age_cutoff >= 0 &&
962 blob_garbage_collection_age_cutoff <= 1) {
963 cf_opts->blob_garbage_collection_age_cutoff =
964 blob_garbage_collection_age_cutoff;
965 } else {
966 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
967 ARG_BLOB_GARBAGE_COLLECTION_AGE_CUTOFF + " must be >= 0 and <= 1.");
968 }
969 }
970
971 double blob_garbage_collection_force_threshold;
972 if (ParseDoubleOption(option_map_,
973 ARG_BLOB_GARBAGE_COLLECTION_FORCE_THRESHOLD,
974 blob_garbage_collection_force_threshold, exec_state_)) {
975 if (blob_garbage_collection_force_threshold >= 0 &&
976 blob_garbage_collection_force_threshold <= 1) {
977 cf_opts->blob_garbage_collection_force_threshold =
978 blob_garbage_collection_force_threshold;
979 } else {
980 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
981 ARG_BLOB_GARBAGE_COLLECTION_FORCE_THRESHOLD +
982 " must be >= 0 and <= 1.");
983 }
984 }
985
986 int blob_compaction_readahead_size;
987 if (ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_BLOB_COMPACTION_READAHEAD_SIZE,
988 blob_compaction_readahead_size, exec_state_)) {
989 if (blob_compaction_readahead_size > 0) {
990 cf_opts->blob_compaction_readahead_size = blob_compaction_readahead_size;
991 } else {
992 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
993 ARG_BLOB_COMPACTION_READAHEAD_SIZE + " must be > 0.");
994 }
995 }
996
997 int blob_file_starting_level;
998 if (ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_BLOB_FILE_STARTING_LEVEL,
999 blob_file_starting_level, exec_state_)) {
1000 if (blob_file_starting_level >= 0) {
1001 cf_opts->blob_file_starting_level = blob_file_starting_level;
1002 } else {
1003 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
1004 ARG_BLOB_FILE_STARTING_LEVEL + " must be >= 0.");
1005 }
1006 }
1007
1008 int prepopulate_blob_cache;
1009 if (ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_PREPOPULATE_BLOB_CACHE,
1010 prepopulate_blob_cache, exec_state_)) {
1011 switch (prepopulate_blob_cache) {
1012 case 0:
1013 cf_opts->prepopulate_blob_cache = PrepopulateBlobCache::kDisable;
1014 break;
1015 case 1:
1016 cf_opts->prepopulate_blob_cache = PrepopulateBlobCache::kFlushOnly;
1017 break;
1018 default:
1019 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
1020 ARG_PREPOPULATE_BLOB_CACHE +
1021 " must be 0 (disable) or 1 (flush only).");
1022 }
1023 }
1024
1025 auto itr = option_map_.find(ARG_AUTO_COMPACTION);
1026 if (itr != option_map_.end()) {
1027 cf_opts->disable_auto_compactions = !StringToBool(itr->second);
1028 }
1029
1030 CompressionType compression_type;
1031 if (ParseCompressionTypeOption(option_map_, ARG_COMPRESSION_TYPE,
1032 compression_type, exec_state_)) {
1033 cf_opts->compression = compression_type;
1034 }
1035
1036 CompressionType blob_compression_type;
1037 if (ParseCompressionTypeOption(option_map_, ARG_BLOB_COMPRESSION_TYPE,
1038 blob_compression_type, exec_state_)) {
1039 cf_opts->blob_compression_type = blob_compression_type;
1040 }
1041
1042 int compression_max_dict_bytes;
1043 if (ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_COMPRESSION_MAX_DICT_BYTES,
1044 compression_max_dict_bytes, exec_state_)) {
1045 if (compression_max_dict_bytes >= 0) {
1046 cf_opts->compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = compression_max_dict_bytes;
1047 } else {
1048 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
1049 ARG_COMPRESSION_MAX_DICT_BYTES + " must be >= 0.");
1050 }
1051 }
1052
1053 int write_buffer_size;
1054 if (ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_WRITE_BUFFER_SIZE, write_buffer_size,
1055 exec_state_)) {
1056 if (write_buffer_size > 0) {
1057 cf_opts->write_buffer_size = write_buffer_size;
1058 } else {
1059 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(ARG_WRITE_BUFFER_SIZE +
1060 " must be > 0.");
1061 }
1062 }
1063
1064 int file_size;
1065 if (ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_FILE_SIZE, file_size, exec_state_)) {
1066 if (file_size > 0) {
1067 cf_opts->target_file_size_base = file_size;
1068 } else {
1069 exec_state_ =
1070 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(ARG_FILE_SIZE + " must be > 0.");
1071 }
1072 }
1073
1074 int fix_prefix_len;
1075 if (ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_FIX_PREFIX_LEN, fix_prefix_len,
1076 exec_state_)) {
1077 if (fix_prefix_len > 0) {
1078 cf_opts->prefix_extractor.reset(
1079 NewFixedPrefixTransform(static_cast<size_t>(fix_prefix_len)));
1080 } else {
1081 exec_state_ =
1082 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(ARG_FIX_PREFIX_LEN + " must be > 0.");
1083 }
1084 }
1085}
1086
1087// First, initializes the options state using the OPTIONS file when enabled.
1088// Second, overrides the options according to the CLI arguments and the
1089// specific subcommand being run.
1090void LDBCommand::PrepareOptions() {
1091 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> column_families_from_options;
1092
1093 if (!create_if_missing_ && try_load_options_) {
1094 config_options_.env = options_.env;
1095 Status s = LoadLatestOptions(config_options_, db_path_, &options_,
1096 &column_families_from_options);
1097 if (!s.ok() && !s.IsNotFound()) {
1098 // Option file exists but load option file error.
1099 std::string current_version = std::to_string(ROCKSDB_MAJOR) + "." +
1100 std::to_string(ROCKSDB_MINOR) + "." +
1101 std::to_string(ROCKSDB_PATCH);
1102 std::string msg =
1103 s.ToString() + "\nThis tool was built with version " +
1104 current_version +
1105 ". If your db is in a different version, please try again "
1106 "with option --" +
1107 LDBCommand::ARG_IGNORE_UNKNOWN_OPTIONS + ".";
1108 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(msg);
1109 db_ = nullptr;
1110 return;
1111 }
1112 if (!options_.wal_dir.empty()) {
1113 if (options_.env->FileExists(options_.wal_dir).IsNotFound()) {
1114 options_.wal_dir = db_path_;
1115 fprintf(
1116 stderr,
1117 "wal_dir loaded from the option file doesn't exist. Ignore it.\n");
1118 }
1119 }
1120
1121 // If merge operator is not set, set a string append operator.
1122 for (auto& cf_entry : column_families_from_options) {
1123 if (!cf_entry.options.merge_operator) {
1124 cf_entry.options.merge_operator =
1125 MergeOperators::CreateStringAppendOperator(':');
1126 }
1127 }
1128 }
1129
1130 if (options_.env == Env::Default()) {
1131 options_.env = config_options_.env;
1132 }
1133
1134 OverrideBaseOptions();
1135 if (exec_state_.IsFailed()) {
1136 return;
1137 }
1138
1139 if (column_families_.empty()) {
1140 // column_families not set. Either set it from MANIFEST or OPTIONS file.
1141 if (column_families_from_options.empty()) {
1142 // Reads the MANIFEST to figure out what column families exist. In this
1143 // case, the option overrides from the CLI argument/specific subcommand
1144 // apply to all column families.
1145 std::vector<std::string> cf_list;
1146 Status st = DB::ListColumnFamilies(options_, db_path_, &cf_list);
1147 // It is possible the DB doesn't exist yet, for "create if not
1148 // existing" case. The failure is ignored here. We rely on DB::Open()
1149 // to give us the correct error message for problem with opening
1150 // existing DB.
1151 if (st.ok() && cf_list.size() > 1) {
1152 // Ignore single column family DB.
1153 for (const auto& cf_name : cf_list) {
1154 column_families_.emplace_back(cf_name, options_);
1155 }
1156 }
1157 } else {
1158 SetColumnFamilies(&column_families_from_options);
1159 }
1160 }
1161
1162 if (!column_families_from_options.empty()) {
1163 // We got column families from the OPTIONS file. In this case, the option
1164 // overrides from the CLI argument/specific subcommand only apply to the
1165 // column family specified by `--column_family_name`.
1166 auto column_families_iter =
1167 std::find_if(column_families_.begin(), column_families_.end(),
1168 [this](const ColumnFamilyDescriptor& cf_desc) {
1169 return cf_desc.name == column_family_name_;
1170 });
1171 if (column_families_iter == column_families_.end()) {
1172 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
1173 "Non-existing column family " + column_family_name_);
1174 return;
1175 }
1176 OverrideBaseCFOptions(&column_families_iter->options);
1177 }
1178}
1179
1180bool LDBCommand::ParseKeyValue(const std::string& line, std::string* key,
1181 std::string* value, bool is_key_hex,
1182 bool is_value_hex) {
1183 size_t pos = line.find(DELIM);
1184 if (pos != std::string::npos) {
1185 *key = line.substr(0, pos);
1186 *value = line.substr(pos + strlen(DELIM));
1187 if (is_key_hex) {
1188 *key = HexToString(*key);
1189 }
1190 if (is_value_hex) {
1191 *value = HexToString(*value);
1192 }
1193 return true;
1194 } else {
1195 return false;
1196 }
1197}
1198
1206bool LDBCommand::ValidateCmdLineOptions() {
1207 for (auto itr = option_map_.begin(); itr != option_map_.end(); ++itr) {
1208 if (std::find(valid_cmd_line_options_.begin(),
1209 valid_cmd_line_options_.end(),
1210 itr->first) == valid_cmd_line_options_.end()) {
1211 fprintf(stderr, "Invalid command-line option %s\n", itr->first.c_str());
1212 return false;
1213 }
1214 }
1215
1216 for (std::vector<std::string>::const_iterator itr = flags_.begin();
1217 itr != flags_.end(); ++itr) {
1218 if (std::find(valid_cmd_line_options_.begin(),
1219 valid_cmd_line_options_.end(),
1220 *itr) == valid_cmd_line_options_.end()) {
1221 fprintf(stderr, "Invalid command-line flag %s\n", itr->c_str());
1222 return false;
1223 }
1224 }
1225
1226 if (!NoDBOpen() && option_map_.find(ARG_DB) == option_map_.end() &&
1227 option_map_.find(ARG_PATH) == option_map_.end()) {
1228 fprintf(stderr, "Either %s or %s must be specified.\n", ARG_DB.c_str(),
1229 ARG_PATH.c_str());
1230 return false;
1231 }
1232
1233 return true;
1234}
1235
1236std::string LDBCommand::HexToString(const std::string& str) {
1237 std::string result;
1238 std::string::size_type len = str.length();
1239 if (len < 2 || str[0] != '0' || str[1] != 'x') {
1240 fprintf(stderr, "Invalid hex input %s. Must start with 0x\n", str.c_str());
1241 throw "Invalid hex input";
1242 }
1243 if (!Slice(str.data() + 2, len - 2).DecodeHex(&result)) {
1244 throw "Invalid hex input";
1245 }
1246 return result;
1247}
1248
1249std::string LDBCommand::StringToHex(const std::string& str) {
1250 std::string result("0x");
1251 result.append(Slice(str).ToString(true));
1252 return result;
1253}

1255std::string LDBCommand::PrintKeyValue(const std::string& key,
1256 const std::string& timestamp,
1257 const std::string& value, bool is_key_hex,
1258 bool is_value_hex,
1259 const Comparator* ucmp) {
1260 std::string result;
1261 result.append(is_key_hex ? StringToHex(key) : key);
1262 if (!timestamp.empty()) {
1263 result.append("|timestamp:");
1264 result.append(ucmp->TimestampToString(timestamp));
1265 }
1266 result.append(DELIM);
1267 result.append(is_value_hex ? StringToHex(value) : value);
1268 return result;
1269}
1270
1271std::string LDBCommand::PrintKeyValue(const std::string& key,
1272 const std::string& timestamp,
1273 const std::string& value, bool is_hex,
1274 const Comparator* ucmp) {
1275 return PrintKeyValue(key, timestamp, value, is_hex, is_hex, ucmp);
1276}
1277
1278std::string LDBCommand::PrintKeyValueOrWideColumns(
1279 const Slice& key, const Slice& timestamp, const Slice& value,
1280 const WideColumns& wide_columns, bool is_key_hex, bool is_value_hex,
1281 const Comparator* ucmp) {
1282 if (wide_columns.empty() ||
1283 WideColumnsHelper::HasDefaultColumnOnly(wide_columns)) {
1284 return PrintKeyValue(key.ToString(), timestamp.ToString(), value.ToString(),
1285 is_key_hex, is_value_hex, ucmp);
1286 }
1287 /*
1288 // Sample plaintext output (first column is kDefaultWideColumnName)
1289 key_1 ==> :foo attr_name1:bar attr_name2:baz
1290
1291 // Sample hex output (first column is kDefaultWideColumnName)
1292 0x6669727374 ==> :0x68656C6C6F 0x617474725F6E616D6531:0x666F6F
1293 */
1294 std::ostringstream oss;
1295 WideColumnsHelper::DumpWideColumns(wide_columns, oss, is_value_hex);
1296 return PrintKeyValue(key.ToString(), timestamp.ToString(), oss.str().c_str(),
1297 is_key_hex, false,
1298 ucmp); // is_value_hex_ is already honored in oss.
1299 // avoid double-hexing it.
1300}

1324
1325bool LDBCommand::IsTryLoadOptions(
1326 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& options,
1327 const std::vector<std::string>& flags) {
1328 if (IsFlagPresent(flags, ARG_TRY_LOAD_OPTIONS)) {
1329 return true;
1330 }
1331 // if `DB` is specified and not explicitly to create a new db, default
1332 // `try_load_options` to true. The user could still disable that by set
1333 // `try_load_options=false`.
1334 // Note: Opening as TTL DB doesn't support `try_load_options`, so it's default
1335 // to false. TODO: TTL_DB may need to fix that, otherwise it's unable to open
1336 // DB which has incompatible setting with default options.
1337 bool default_val = (options.find(ARG_DB) != options.end()) &&
1338 !IsFlagPresent(flags, ARG_CREATE_IF_MISSING) &&
1339 !IsFlagPresent(flags, ARG_TTL);
1340 return ParseBooleanOption(options, ARG_TRY_LOAD_OPTIONS, default_val);
1341}
1342
1343bool LDBCommand::ParseBooleanOption(
1344 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& options,
1345 const std::string& option, bool default_val) {
1346 auto itr = options.find(option);
1347 if (itr != options.end()) {
1348 std::string option_val = itr->second;
1349 return StringToBool(itr->second);
1350 }
1351 return default_val;
1352}
1353
1354bool LDBCommand::StringToBool(std::string val) {
1355 std::transform(val.begin(), val.end(), val.begin(),
1356 [](char ch) -> char { return (char)::tolower(ch); });
1357
1358 if (val == "true") {
1359 return true;
1360 } else if (val == "false") {
1361 return false;
1362 } else {
1363 throw "Invalid value for boolean argument";
1364 }
1365}

1367CompactorCommand::CompactorCommand(
1368 const std::vector<std::string>& /*params*/,
1369 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& options,
1370 const std::vector<std::string>& flags)
1371 : LDBCommand(options, flags, false,
1372 BuildCmdLineOptions({ARG_FROM, ARG_TO, ARG_HEX, ARG_KEY_HEX,
1373 ARG_VALUE_HEX, ARG_TTL})),
1374 null_from_(true),
1375 null_to_(true) {

1378 null_from_ = false;
1379 from_ = itr->second;
1380 }
1381
1382 itr = options.find(ARG_TO);
1383 if (itr != options.end()) {
1384 null_to_ = false;
1385 to_ = itr->second;
1386 }
1387
1388 if (is_key_hex_) {
1389 if (!null_from_) {
1390 from_ = HexToString(from_);
1391 }
1392 if (!null_to_) {
1393 to_ = HexToString(to_);
1394 }
1395 }
1396}

1398void CompactorCommand::Help(std::string& ret) {
1399 ret.append(" ");
1400 ret.append(CompactorCommand::Name());
1401 ret.append(HelpRangeCmdArgs());
1402 ret.append("\n");
1403}
1404
1405void CompactorCommand::DoCommand() {
1406 if (!db_) {
1407 assert(GetExecuteState().IsFailed());
1408 return;
1409 }
1410
1411 Slice* begin = nullptr;
1412 Slice* end = nullptr;
1413 if (!null_from_) {
1414 begin = new Slice(from_);
1415 }
1416 if (!null_to_) {
1417 end = new Slice(to_);
1418 }
1419
1420 CompactRangeOptions cro;
1421 cro.bottommost_level_compaction = BottommostLevelCompaction::kForceOptimized;
1422
1423 Status s = db_->CompactRange(cro, GetCfHandle(), begin, end);
1424 if (!s.ok()) {
1425 std::stringstream oss;
1426 oss << "Compaction failed: " << s.ToString();
1427 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(oss.str());
1428 } else {
1429 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Succeed("");
1430 }
1431
1432 delete begin;
1433 delete end;
1434}

1471 options_.create_if_missing = create_if_missing_;
1472 if (bulk_load_) {
1473 options_.PrepareForBulkLoad();
1474 }

1476
1477void DBLoaderCommand::DoCommand() {
1478 if (!db_) {
1479 assert(GetExecuteState().IsFailed());
1480 return;
1481 }
1482
1483 WriteOptions write_options;
1484 if (disable_wal_) {
1485 write_options.disableWAL = true;
1486 }
1487
1488 int bad_lines = 0;
1489 std::string line;
1490 // prefer ifstream getline performance vs that from std::cin istream
1491 std::ifstream ifs_stdin("/dev/stdin");
1492 std::istream* istream_p = ifs_stdin.is_open() ? &ifs_stdin : &std::cin;
1493 Status s;
1494 while (s.ok() && getline(*istream_p, line, '\n')) {
1495 std::string key;
1496 std::string value;
1497 if (ParseKeyValue(line, &key, &value, is_key_hex_, is_value_hex_)) {
1498 s = db_->Put(write_options, GetCfHandle(), Slice(key), Slice(value));
1499 } else if (0 == line.find("Keys in range:")) {
1500 // ignore this line
1501 } else if (0 == line.find("Created bg thread 0x")) {
1502 // ignore this line
1503 } else {
1504 bad_lines++;
1505 }
1506 }
1507
1508 if (bad_lines > 0) {
1509 std::cout << "Warning: " << bad_lines << " bad lines ignored." << std::endl;
1510 }
1511 if (!s.ok()) {
1512 std::stringstream oss;
1513 oss << "Load failed: " << s.ToString();
1514 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(oss.str());
1515 }
1516 if (compact_ && s.ok()) {
1517 s = db_->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), GetCfHandle(), nullptr,
1518 nullptr);
1519 }
1520 if (!s.ok()) {
1521 std::stringstream oss;
1522 oss << "Compaction failed: " << s.ToString();
1523 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(oss.str());
1524 }
1525}

1531void DumpManifestFile(Options options, std::string file, bool verbose, bool hex,
1532 bool json,
1533 const std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor>& cf_descs) {
1534 EnvOptions sopt;
1535 std::string dbname("dummy");
1536 std::shared_ptr<Cache> tc(NewLRUCache(options.max_open_files - 10,
1537 options.table_cache_numshardbits));
1538 // Notice we are using the default options not through SanitizeOptions(),
1539 // if VersionSet::DumpManifest() depends on any option done by
1540 // SanitizeOptions(), we need to initialize it manually.
1541 options.db_paths.emplace_back("dummy", 0);
1542 options.num_levels = 64;
1543 WriteController wc(options.delayed_write_rate);
1544 WriteBufferManager wb(options.db_write_buffer_size);
1545 ImmutableDBOptions immutable_db_options(options);
1546 VersionSet versions(dbname, &immutable_db_options, sopt, tc.get(), &wb, &wc,
1547 /*block_cache_tracer=*/nullptr, /*io_tracer=*/nullptr,
1548 /*db_id=*/"", /*db_session_id=*/"",
1549 options.daily_offpeak_time_utc,
1550 /*error_handler=*/nullptr, /*read_only=*/true);
1551 Status s = versions.DumpManifest(options, file, verbose, hex, json, cf_descs);
1552 if (!s.ok()) {
1553 fprintf(stderr, "Error in processing file %s %s\n", file.c_str(),
1554 s.ToString().c_str());
1555 }
1556}

1567 ret.append(" [--" + ARG_VERBOSE + "]");
1568 ret.append(" [--" + ARG_JSON + "]");

1572
1573ManifestDumpCommand::ManifestDumpCommand(
1574 const std::vector<std::string>& /*params*/,
1575 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& options,
1576 const std::vector<std::string>& flags)
1577 : LDBCommand(
1578 options, flags, false,
1579 BuildCmdLineOptions({ARG_VERBOSE, ARG_PATH, ARG_HEX, ARG_JSON})),
1580 verbose_(false),
1581 json_(false) {
1582 verbose_ = IsFlagPresent(flags, ARG_VERBOSE);
1583 json_ = IsFlagPresent(flags, ARG_JSON);
1584
1585 auto itr = options.find(ARG_PATH);
1586 if (itr != options.end()) {
1587 path_ = itr->second;
1588 if (path_.empty()) {
1589 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed("--path: missing pathname");
1590 }
1591 }
1592}
1593
1594void ManifestDumpCommand::DoCommand() {
1595 PrepareOptions();
1596 std::string manifestfile;
1597
1598 if (!path_.empty()) {
1599 manifestfile = path_;
1600 } else {
1601 // We need to find the manifest file by searching the directory
1602 // containing the db for files of the form MANIFEST_[0-9]+
1603
1604 std::vector<std::string> files;
1605 Status s = options_.env->GetChildren(db_path_, &files);
1606 if (!s.ok()) {
1607 std::string err_msg = s.ToString();
1608 err_msg.append(": Failed to list the content of ");
1609 err_msg.append(db_path_);
1610 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(err_msg);
1611 return;
1612 }
1613 const std::string kManifestNamePrefix = "MANIFEST-";
1614 std::string matched_file;
1615#ifdef OS_WIN
1616 const char kPathDelim = '\\';
1617#else
1618 const char kPathDelim = '/';
1619#endif
1620 for (const auto& file_path : files) {
1621 // Some Env::GetChildren() return absolute paths. Some directories' path
1622 // end with path delim, e.g. '/' or '\\'.
1623 size_t pos = file_path.find_last_of(kPathDelim);
1624 if (pos == file_path.size() - 1) {
1625 continue;
1626 }
1627 std::string fname;
1628 if (pos != std::string::npos) {
1629 // Absolute path.
1630 fname.assign(file_path, pos + 1, file_path.size() - pos - 1);
1631 } else {
1632 fname = file_path;
1633 }
1634 uint64_t file_num = 0;
1635 FileType file_type = kWalFile; // Just for initialization
1636 if (ParseFileName(fname, &file_num, &file_type) &&
1637 file_type == kDescriptorFile) {
1638 if (!matched_file.empty()) {
1639 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
1640 "Multiple MANIFEST files found; use --path to select one");
1641 return;
1642 } else {
1643 matched_file.swap(fname);
1644 }
1645 }
1646 }
1647 if (matched_file.empty()) {
1648 std::string err_msg("No MANIFEST found in ");
1649 err_msg.append(db_path_);
1650 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(err_msg);
1651 return;
1652 }
1653 if (db_path_.back() != '/') {
1654 db_path_.append("/");
1655 }
1656 manifestfile = db_path_ + matched_file;
1657 }
1658
1659 if (verbose_) {
1660 fprintf(stdout, "Processing Manifest file %s\n", manifestfile.c_str());
1661 }
1662
1663 DumpManifestFile(options_, manifestfile, verbose_, is_key_hex_, json_,
1664 column_families_);
1665
1666 if (verbose_) {
1667 fprintf(stdout, "Processing Manifest file %s done\n", manifestfile.c_str());
1668 }
1669}

1674Status GetLiveFilesChecksumInfoFromVersionSet(Options options,
1675 const std::string& db_path,
1676 FileChecksumList* checksum_list) {
1677 EnvOptions sopt;
1678 Status s;
1679 std::string dbname(db_path);
1680 std::shared_ptr<Cache> tc(NewLRUCache(options.max_open_files - 10,
1681 options.table_cache_numshardbits));
1682 // Notice we are using the default options not through SanitizeOptions(),
1683 // if VersionSet::GetLiveFilesChecksumInfo depends on any option done by
1684 // SanitizeOptions(), we need to initialize it manually.
1685 options.db_paths.emplace_back(db_path, 0);
1686 options.num_levels = 64;
1687 WriteController wc(options.delayed_write_rate);
1688 WriteBufferManager wb(options.db_write_buffer_size);
1689 ImmutableDBOptions immutable_db_options(options);
1690 VersionSet versions(dbname, &immutable_db_options, sopt, tc.get(), &wb, &wc,
1691 /*block_cache_tracer=*/nullptr, /*io_tracer=*/nullptr,
1692 /*db_id=*/"", /*db_session_id=*/"",
1693 options.daily_offpeak_time_utc,
1694 /*error_handler=*/nullptr, /*read_only=*/true);
1695 std::vector<std::string> cf_name_list;
1696 s = versions.ListColumnFamilies(&cf_name_list, db_path,
1697 immutable_db_options.fs.get());
1698 if (s.ok()) {
1699 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> cf_list;
1700 for (const auto& name : cf_name_list) {
1701 cf_list.emplace_back(name, ColumnFamilyOptions(options));
1702 }
1703 s = versions.Recover(cf_list, true);
1704 }
1705 if (s.ok()) {
1706 s = versions.GetLiveFilesChecksumInfo(checksum_list);
1707 }
1708 return s;
1709}

1722FileChecksumDumpCommand::FileChecksumDumpCommand(
1723 const std::vector<std::string>& /*params*/,
1724 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& options,
1725 const std::vector<std::string>& flags)
1726 : LDBCommand(options, flags, false,
1727 BuildCmdLineOptions({ARG_PATH, ARG_HEX})) {
1728 auto itr = options.find(ARG_PATH);
1729 if (itr != options.end()) {
1730 path_ = itr->second;
1731 if (path_.empty()) {
1732 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed("--path: missing pathname");
1733 }
1734 }
1735 is_checksum_hex_ = IsFlagPresent(flags, ARG_HEX);
1736}
1737
1738void FileChecksumDumpCommand::DoCommand() {
1739 PrepareOptions();
1740 // print out the checksum information in the following format:
1741 // sst file number, checksum function name, checksum value
1742 // sst file number, checksum function name, checksum value
1743 // ......
1744
1745 std::unique_ptr<FileChecksumList> checksum_list(NewFileChecksumList());
1746 Status s = GetLiveFilesChecksumInfoFromVersionSet(options_, db_path_,
1747 checksum_list.get());
1748 if (s.ok() && checksum_list != nullptr) {
1749 std::vector<uint64_t> file_numbers;
1750 std::vector<std::string> checksums;
1751 std::vector<std::string> checksum_func_names;
1752 s = checksum_list->GetAllFileChecksums(&file_numbers, &checksums,
1753 &checksum_func_names);
1754 if (s.ok()) {
1755 for (size_t i = 0; i < file_numbers.size(); i++) {
1756 assert(i < file_numbers.size());
1757 assert(i < checksums.size());
1758 assert(i < checksum_func_names.size());
1759 std::string checksum;
1760 if (is_checksum_hex_) {
1761 checksum = StringToHex(checksums[i]);
1762 } else {
1763 checksum = std::move(checksums[i]);
1764 }
1765 fprintf(stdout, "%" PRId64 ", %s, %s\n", file_numbers[i],
1766 checksum_func_names[i].c_str(), checksum.c_str());
1767 }
1768 fprintf(stdout, "Print SST file checksum information finished \n");
1769 }
1770 }
1771
1772 if (!s.ok()) {
1773 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(s.ToString());
1774 }
1775}

1786GetPropertyCommand::GetPropertyCommand(
1787 const std::vector<std::string>& params,
1788 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& options,
1789 const std::vector<std::string>& flags)
1790 : LDBCommand(options, flags, true, BuildCmdLineOptions({})) {
1791 if (params.size() != 1) {
1792 exec_state_ =
1793 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed("property name must be specified");
1794 } else {
1795 property_ = params[0];
1796 }

1798
1799void GetPropertyCommand::DoCommand() {
1800 if (!db_) {
1801 assert(GetExecuteState().IsFailed());
1802 return;
1803 }
1804
1805 std::map<std::string, std::string> value_map;
1806 std::string value;
1807
1808 // Rather than having different ldb command for map properties vs. string
1809 // properties, we simply try Map property first. (This order only chosen
1810 // because I prefer the map-style output for
1811 // "rocksdb.aggregated-table-properties".)
1812 if (db_->GetMapProperty(GetCfHandle(), property_, &value_map)) {
1813 if (value_map.empty()) {
1814 fprintf(stdout, "%s: <empty map>\n", property_.c_str());
1815 } else {
1816 for (auto& e : value_map) {
1817 fprintf(stdout, "%s.%s: %s\n", property_.c_str(), e.first.c_str(),
1818 e.second.c_str());
1819 }
1820 }
1821 } else if (db_->GetProperty(GetCfHandle(), property_, &value)) {
1822 fprintf(stdout, "%s: %s\n", property_.c_str(), value.c_str());
1823 } else {
1824 exec_state_ =
1825 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed("failed to get property: " + property_);
1826 }
1827}

1946// This function only called when it's the sane case of >1 buckets in time-range
1947// Also called only when timekv falls between ttl_start and ttl_end provided
1948void IncBucketCounts(std::vector<uint64_t>& bucket_counts, int ttl_start,
1949 int time_range, int bucket_size, int timekv,
1950 int num_buckets) {
1951#ifdef NDEBUG
1952 (void)time_range;
1953 (void)num_buckets;
1954#endif
1955 assert(time_range > 0 && timekv >= ttl_start && bucket_size > 0 &&
1956 timekv < (ttl_start + time_range) && num_buckets > 1);
1957 int bucket = (timekv - ttl_start) / bucket_size;
1958 bucket_counts[bucket]++;
1959}
1960
1961void PrintBucketCounts(const std::vector<uint64_t>& bucket_counts,
1962 int ttl_start, int ttl_end, int bucket_size,
1963 int num_buckets) {
1964 int time_point = ttl_start;
1965 for (int i = 0; i < num_buckets - 1; i++, time_point += bucket_size) {
1966 fprintf(stdout, "Keys in range %s to %s : %lu\n",
1967 TimeToHumanString(time_point).c_str(),
1968 TimeToHumanString(time_point + bucket_size).c_str(),
1969 (unsigned long)bucket_counts[i]);
1970 }
1971 fprintf(stdout, "Keys in range %s to %s : %lu\n",
1972 TimeToHumanString(time_point).c_str(),
1973 TimeToHumanString(ttl_end).c_str(),
1974 (unsigned long)bucket_counts[num_buckets - 1]);
1975}

2044void InternalDumpCommand::DoCommand() {
2045 if (!db_) {
2046 assert(GetExecuteState().IsFailed());
2047 return;
2048 }
2049 ColumnFamilyHandle* cfh = GetCfHandle();
2050 const Comparator* ucmp = cfh->GetComparator();
2051 size_t ts_sz = ucmp->timestamp_size();
2052 if (print_stats_) {
2053 std::string stats;
2054 if (db_->GetProperty(cfh, "rocksdb.stats", &stats)) {
2055 fprintf(stdout, "%s\n", stats.c_str());
2056 }
2057 }
2058
2059 // Cast as DBImpl to get internal iterator
2060 std::vector<KeyVersion> key_versions;
2061 Status st = GetAllKeyVersions(db_, GetCfHandle(), from_, to_, max_keys_,
2062 &key_versions);
2063 if (!st.ok()) {
2064 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(st.ToString());
2065 return;
2066 }
2067 std::string rtype1, rtype2, row, val;
2068 rtype2 = "";
2069 uint64_t c = 0;
2070 uint64_t s1 = 0, s2 = 0;
2071
2072 long long count = 0;
2073 for (auto& key_version : key_versions) {
2074 ValueType value_type = static_cast<ValueType>(key_version.type);
2075 InternalKey ikey(key_version.user_key, key_version.sequence, value_type);
2076 Slice user_key_without_ts = ikey.user_key();
2077 if (ts_sz > 0) {
2078 user_key_without_ts.remove_suffix(ts_sz);
2079 }
2080 if (has_to_ && ucmp->Compare(user_key_without_ts, to_) == 0) {
2081 // GetAllKeyVersions() includes keys with user key `to_`, but idump has
2082 // traditionally excluded such keys.
2083 break;
2084 }
2085 ++count;
2086 int k;
2087 if (count_delim_) {
2088 rtype1 = "";
2089 s1 = 0;
2090 row = ikey.Encode().ToString();
2091 val = key_version.value;
2092 for (k = 0; row[k] != '\x01' && row[k] != '\0'; k++) {
2093 s1++;
2094 }
2095 for (k = 0; val[k] != '\x01' && val[k] != '\0'; k++) {
2096 s1++;
2097 }
2098 for (int j = 0; row[j] != delim_[0] && row[j] != '\0' && row[j] != '\x01';
2099 j++) {
2100 rtype1 += row[j];
2101 }
2102 if (rtype2.compare("") && rtype2.compare(rtype1) != 0) {
2103 fprintf(stdout, "%s => count:%" PRIu64 "\tsize:%" PRIu64 "\n",
2104 rtype2.c_str(), c, s2);
2105 c = 1;
2106 s2 = s1;
2107 rtype2 = rtype1;
2108 } else {
2109 c++;
2110 s2 += s1;
2111 rtype2 = rtype1;
2112 }
2113 }
2114
2115 if (!count_only_ && !count_delim_) {
2116 std::string key = ikey.DebugString(is_key_hex_, ucmp);
2117 Slice value(key_version.value);
2118 if (!decode_blob_index_ || value_type != kTypeBlobIndex) {
2119 if (value_type == kTypeWideColumnEntity) {
2120 std::ostringstream oss;
2121 const Status s = WideColumnsHelper::DumpSliceAsWideColumns(
2122 value, oss, is_value_hex_);
2123 if (!s.ok()) {
2124 fprintf(stderr, "%s => error deserializing wide columns\n",
2125 key.c_str());
2126 } else {
2127 fprintf(stdout, "%s => %s\n", key.c_str(), oss.str().c_str());
2128 }
2129 } else {
2130 fprintf(stdout, "%s => %s\n", key.c_str(),
2131 value.ToString(is_value_hex_).c_str());
2132 }
2133 } else {
2134 BlobIndex blob_index;
2135
2136 const Status s = blob_index.DecodeFrom(value);
2137 if (!s.ok()) {
2138 fprintf(stderr, "%s => error decoding blob index =>\n", key.c_str());
2139 } else {
2140 fprintf(stdout, "%s => %s\n", key.c_str(),
2141 blob_index.DebugString(is_value_hex_).c_str());
2142 }
2143 }
2144 }
2145
2146 // Terminate if maximum number of keys have been dumped
2147 if (max_keys_ > 0 && count >= max_keys_) {
2148 break;
2149 }
2150 }
2151 if (count_delim_) {
2152 fprintf(stdout, "%s => count:%" PRIu64 "\tsize:%" PRIu64 "\n",
2153 rtype2.c_str(), c, s2);
2154 } else {
2155 fprintf(stdout, "Internal keys in range: %lld\n", count);
2156 }
2157}

2272void DBDumperCommand::DoCommand() {
2273 if (!db_) {
2274 assert(!path_.empty());
2275 std::string fileName = GetFileNameFromPath(path_);
2276 uint64_t number;
2277 FileType type;
2278
2279 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Succeed("");
2280
2281 if (!ParseFileName(fileName, &number, &type)) {
2282 exec_state_ =
2283 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed("Can't parse file type: " + path_);
2284 return;
2285 }
2286
2287 switch (type) {
2288 case kWalFile:
2289 // TODO(myabandeh): allow configuring is_write_commited
2290 DumpWalFiles(options_, path_, /* print_header_ */ true,
2291 /* print_values_ */ true,
2292 /* only_print_seqno_gaps */ false,
2293 true /* is_write_commited */, ucmps_, &exec_state_);
2294 break;
2295 case kTableFile:
2296 DumpSstFile(options_, path_, is_key_hex_, /* show_properties */ true,
2297 decode_blob_index_, from_, to_);
2298 break;
2299 case kDescriptorFile:
2300 DumpManifestFile(options_, path_, /* verbose_ */ false, is_key_hex_,
2301 /* json_ */ false, column_families_);
2302 break;
2303 case kBlobFile:
2304 DumpBlobFile(path_, is_key_hex_, is_value_hex_,
2305 dump_uncompressed_blobs_);
2306 break;
2307 default:
2308 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
2309 "File type not supported: " + path_);
2310 break;
2311 }
2312
2313 } else {
2314 DoDumpCommand();
2315 }

2317
2318void DBDumperCommand::DoDumpCommand() {
2319 assert(nullptr != db_);
2320 assert(path_.empty());
2321
2322 // Parse command line args
2323 uint64_t count = 0;
2324 if (print_stats_) {
2325 std::string stats;
2326 if (db_->GetProperty("rocksdb.stats", &stats)) {
2327 fprintf(stdout, "%s\n", stats.c_str());
2328 }
2329 }
2330
2331 // Setup key iterator
2332 ReadOptions scan_read_opts;
2333 Slice read_timestamp;
2334 ColumnFamilyHandle* cfh = GetCfHandle();
2335 const Comparator* ucmp = cfh->GetComparator();
2336 size_t ts_sz = ucmp->timestamp_size();
2337 if (ucmp->timestamp_size() > 0) {
2338 read_timestamp = ucmp->GetMaxTimestamp();
2339 scan_read_opts.timestamp = &read_timestamp;
2340 }
2341 scan_read_opts.total_order_seek = true;
2342 Iterator* iter = db_->NewIterator(scan_read_opts, cfh);
2343 Status st = iter->status();
2344 if (!st.ok()) {
2345 exec_state_ =
2346 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed("Iterator error." + st.ToString());
2347 }
2348
2349 if (!null_from_) {
2350 iter->Seek(from_);
2351 } else {
2352 iter->SeekToFirst();
2353 }
2354
2355 int max_keys = max_keys_;
2356 int ttl_start;
2357 if (!ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_TTL_START, ttl_start, exec_state_)) {
2358 ttl_start = DBWithTTLImpl::kMinTimestamp; // TTL introduction time
2359 }
2360 int ttl_end;
2361 if (!ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_TTL_END, ttl_end, exec_state_)) {
2362 ttl_end = DBWithTTLImpl::kMaxTimestamp; // Max time allowed by TTL feature
2363 }
2364 if (ttl_end < ttl_start) {
2365 fprintf(stderr, "Error: End time can't be less than start time\n");
2366 delete iter;
2367 return;
2368 }
2369 int time_range = ttl_end - ttl_start;
2370 int bucket_size;
2371 if (!ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_TTL_BUCKET, bucket_size, exec_state_) ||
2372 bucket_size <= 0) {
2373 bucket_size = time_range; // Will have just 1 bucket by default
2374 }
2375 // cretaing variables for row count of each type
2376 std::string rtype1, rtype2, row, val;
2377 rtype2 = "";
2378 uint64_t c = 0;
2379 uint64_t s1 = 0, s2 = 0;
2380
2381 // At this point, bucket_size=0 => time_range=0
2382 int num_buckets = (bucket_size >= time_range)
2383 ? 1
2384 : ((time_range + bucket_size - 1) / bucket_size);
2385 std::vector<uint64_t> bucket_counts(num_buckets, 0);
2386 if (is_db_ttl_ && !count_only_ && timestamp_ && !count_delim_) {
2387 fprintf(stdout, "Dumping key-values from %s to %s\n",
2388 TimeToHumanString(ttl_start).c_str(),
2389 TimeToHumanString(ttl_end).c_str());
2390 }
2391
2392 HistogramImpl vsize_hist;
2393
2394 for (; iter->Valid(); iter->Next()) {
2395 int rawtime = 0;
2396 // If end marker was specified, we stop before it
2397 if (!null_to_ && ucmp->Compare(iter->key(), to_) >= 0) {
2398 break;
2399 }
2400 // Terminate if maximum number of keys have been dumped
2401 if (max_keys == 0) {
2402 break;
2403 }
2404 if (is_db_ttl_) {
2405 TtlIterator* it_ttl = static_cast_with_check<TtlIterator>(iter);
2406 rawtime = it_ttl->ttl_timestamp();
2407 if (rawtime < ttl_start || rawtime >= ttl_end) {
2408 continue;
2409 }
2410 }
2411 if (max_keys > 0) {
2412 --max_keys;
2413 }
2414 if (is_db_ttl_ && num_buckets > 1) {
2415 IncBucketCounts(bucket_counts, ttl_start, time_range, bucket_size,
2416 rawtime, num_buckets);
2417 }
2418 ++count;
2419 if (count_delim_) {
2420 rtype1 = "";
2421 row = iter->key().ToString();
2422 val = iter->value().ToString();
2423 s1 = row.size() + val.size();
2424 for (int j = 0; row[j] != delim_[0] && row[j] != '\0'; j++) {
2425 rtype1 += row[j];
2426 }
2427 if (rtype2.compare("") && rtype2.compare(rtype1) != 0) {
2428 fprintf(stdout, "%s => count:%" PRIu64 "\tsize:%" PRIu64 "\n",
2429 rtype2.c_str(), c, s2);
2430 c = 1;
2431 s2 = s1;
2432 rtype2 = rtype1;
2433 } else {
2434 c++;
2435 s2 += s1;
2436 rtype2 = rtype1;
2437 }
2438 }
2439
2440 if (count_only_) {
2441 vsize_hist.Add(iter->value().size());
2442 }
2443
2444 if (!count_only_ && !count_delim_) {
2445 if (is_db_ttl_ && timestamp_) {
2446 fprintf(stdout, "%s ", TimeToHumanString(rawtime).c_str());
2447 }
2448 // (TODO) TTL Iterator does not support wide columns yet.
2449 std::string str =
2450 is_db_ttl_
2451 ? PrintKeyValue(iter->key().ToString(),
2452 ts_sz == 0 ? "" : iter->timestamp().ToString(),
2453 iter->value().ToString(), is_key_hex_,
2454 is_value_hex_, ucmp)
2455 : PrintKeyValueOrWideColumns(
2456 iter->key(), ts_sz == 0 ? "" : iter->timestamp().ToString(),
2457 iter->value(), iter->columns(), is_key_hex_, is_value_hex_,
2458 ucmp);
2459 fprintf(stdout, "%s\n", str.c_str());
2460 }
2461 }
2462
2463 if (num_buckets > 1 && is_db_ttl_) {
2464 PrintBucketCounts(bucket_counts, ttl_start, ttl_end, bucket_size,
2465 num_buckets);
2466 } else if (count_delim_) {
2467 fprintf(stdout, "%s => count:%" PRIu64 "\tsize:%" PRIu64 "\n",
2468 rtype2.c_str(), c, s2);
2469 } else {
2470 fprintf(stdout, "Keys in range: %" PRIu64 "\n", count);
2471 }
2472
2473 if (count_only_) {
2474 fprintf(stdout, "Value size distribution: \n");
2475 fprintf(stdout, "%s\n", vsize_hist.ToString().c_str());
2476 }
2477 // Clean up
2478 delete iter;
2479}

2481const std::string ReduceDBLevelsCommand::ARG_NEW_LEVELS = "new_levels";
2482const std::string ReduceDBLevelsCommand::ARG_PRINT_OLD_LEVELS =
2483 "print_old_levels";
2484
2485ReduceDBLevelsCommand::ReduceDBLevelsCommand(
2486 const std::vector<std::string>& /*params*/,
2487 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& options,
2488 const std::vector<std::string>& flags)
2489 : LDBCommand(options, flags, false,
2490 BuildCmdLineOptions({ARG_NEW_LEVELS, ARG_PRINT_OLD_LEVELS})),
2491 old_levels_(1 << 7),
2492 new_levels_(-1),
2493 print_old_levels_(false) {
2494 ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_NEW_LEVELS, new_levels_, exec_state_);
2495 print_old_levels_ = IsFlagPresent(flags, ARG_PRINT_OLD_LEVELS);
2496
2497 if (new_levels_ <= 0) {
2498 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
2499 " Use --" + ARG_NEW_LEVELS + " to specify a new level number\n");
2500 }
2501}

2533
2534Status ReduceDBLevelsCommand::GetOldNumOfLevels(Options& opt, int* levels) {
2535 ImmutableDBOptions db_options(opt);
2536 EnvOptions soptions;
2537 std::shared_ptr<Cache> tc(
2538 NewLRUCache(opt.max_open_files - 10, opt.table_cache_numshardbits));
2539 const InternalKeyComparator cmp(opt.comparator);
2540 WriteController wc(opt.delayed_write_rate);
2541 WriteBufferManager wb(opt.db_write_buffer_size);
2542 VersionSet versions(db_path_, &db_options, soptions, tc.get(), &wb, &wc,
2543 /*block_cache_tracer=*/nullptr, /*io_tracer=*/nullptr,
2544 /*db_id=*/"", /*db_session_id=*/"",
2545 opt.daily_offpeak_time_utc,
2546 /*error_handler=*/nullptr, /*read_only=*/true);
2547 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> dummy;
2548 ColumnFamilyDescriptor dummy_descriptor(kDefaultColumnFamilyName,
2549 ColumnFamilyOptions(opt));
2550 dummy.push_back(dummy_descriptor);
2551 // We rely the VersionSet::Recover to tell us the internal data structures
2552 // in the db. And the Recover() should never do any change
2553 // (like LogAndApply) to the manifest file.
2554 Status st = versions.Recover(dummy);
2555 if (!st.ok()) {
2556 return st;
2557 }
2558 int max = -1;
2559 auto default_cfd = versions.GetColumnFamilySet()->GetDefault();
2560 for (int i = 0; i < default_cfd->NumberLevels(); i++) {
2561 if (default_cfd->current()->storage_info()->NumLevelFiles(i)) {
2562 max = i;
2563 }
2564 }
2565
2566 *levels = max + 1;
2567 return st;
2568}
2569
2570void ReduceDBLevelsCommand::DoCommand() {
2571 if (new_levels_ <= 1) {
2572 exec_state_ =
2573 LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed("Invalid number of levels.\n");
2574 return;
2575 }
2576
2577 Status st;
2578 PrepareOptions();
2579 int old_level_num = -1;
2580 st = GetOldNumOfLevels(options_, &old_level_num);
2581 if (!st.ok()) {
2582 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(st.ToString());
2583 return;
2584 }
2585
2586 if (print_old_levels_) {
2587 fprintf(stdout, "The old number of levels in use is %d\n", old_level_num);
2588 }
2589
2590 if (old_level_num <= new_levels_) {
2591 return;
2592 }
2593
2594 old_levels_ = old_level_num;
2595
2596 OpenDB();
2597 if (exec_state_.IsFailed()) {
2598 return;
2599 }
2600 assert(db_ != nullptr);
2601 // Compact the whole DB to put all files to the highest level.
2602 fprintf(stdout, "Compacting the db...\n");
2603 st =
2604 db_->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), GetCfHandle(), nullptr, nullptr);
2605
2606 CloseDB();
2607
2608 if (st.ok()) {
2609 EnvOptions soptions;
2610 st = VersionSet::ReduceNumberOfLevels(db_path_, &options_, soptions,
2611 new_levels_);
2612 }
2613 if (!st.ok()) {
2614 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(st.ToString());
2615 return;
2616 }
2617}

2619const std::string ChangeCompactionStyleCommand::ARG_OLD_COMPACTION_STYLE =
2620 "old_compaction_style";
2621const std::string ChangeCompactionStyleCommand::ARG_NEW_COMPACTION_STYLE =
2622 "new_compaction_style";
2623
2624ChangeCompactionStyleCommand::ChangeCompactionStyleCommand(
2625 const std::vector<std::string>& /*params*/,
2626 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& options,
2627 const std::vector<std::string>& flags)
2628 : LDBCommand(options, flags, false,
2629 BuildCmdLineOptions(
2630 {ARG_OLD_COMPACTION_STYLE, ARG_NEW_COMPACTION_STYLE})),
2631 old_compaction_style_(-1),
2632 new_compaction_style_(-1) {
2633 ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_OLD_COMPACTION_STYLE, old_compaction_style_,

2636 old_compaction_style_ != kCompactionStyleUniversal) {
2637 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
2638 "Use --" + ARG_OLD_COMPACTION_STYLE + " to specify old compaction " +
2639 "style. Check ldb help for proper compaction style value.\n");
2640 return;
2641 }
2642
2643 ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_NEW_COMPACTION_STYLE, new_compaction_style_,
2644 exec_state_);
2645 if (new_compaction_style_ != kCompactionStyleLevel &&
2646 new_compaction_style_ != kCompactionStyleUniversal) {
2647 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
2648 "Use --" + ARG_NEW_COMPACTION_STYLE + " to specify new compaction " +
2649 "style. Check ldb help for proper compaction style value.\n");
2650 return;
2651 }
2652
2653 if (new_compaction_style_ == old_compaction_style_) {
2654 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
2655 "Old compaction style is the same as new compaction style. "
2656 "Nothing to do.\n");
2657 return;
2658 }
2659
2660 if (old_compaction_style_ == kCompactionStyleUniversal &&
2661 new_compaction_style_ == kCompactionStyleLevel) {
2662 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
2663 "Convert from universal compaction to level compaction. "
2664 "Nothing to do.\n");
2665 return;
2666 }
2667}

2673 "for level compaction, 1 for universal compaction>");

2675 "for level compaction, 1 for universal compaction>");
2676 ret.append("\n");
2677}
2678
2679void ChangeCompactionStyleCommand::OverrideBaseCFOptions(
2680 ColumnFamilyOptions* cf_opts) {
2681 LDBCommand::OverrideBaseCFOptions(cf_opts);
2682 if (old_compaction_style_ == kCompactionStyleLevel &&
2683 new_compaction_style_ == kCompactionStyleUniversal) {
2684 // In order to convert from level compaction to universal compaction, we
2685 // need to compact all data into a single file and move it to level 0.
2686 cf_opts->disable_auto_compactions = true;
2687 cf_opts->target_file_size_base = INT_MAX;
2688 cf_opts->target_file_size_multiplier = 1;
2689 cf_opts->max_bytes_for_level_base = INT_MAX;
2690 cf_opts->max_bytes_for_level_multiplier = 1;
2691 }
2692}
2693
2694void ChangeCompactionStyleCommand::DoCommand() {
2695 if (!db_) {
2696 assert(GetExecuteState().IsFailed());
2697 return;
2698 }
2699 // print db stats before we have made any change
2700 std::string property;
2701 std::string files_per_level;
2702 for (int i = 0; i < db_->NumberLevels(GetCfHandle()); i++) {
2703 db_->GetProperty(GetCfHandle(),
2704 "rocksdb.num-files-at-level" + std::to_string(i),
2705 &property);
2706
2707 // format print string
2708 char buf[100];
2709 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%s%s", (i ? "," : ""), property.c_str());
2710 files_per_level += buf;
2711 }
2712 fprintf(stdout, "files per level before compaction: %s\n",
2713 files_per_level.c_str());
2714
2715 // manual compact into a single file and move the file to level 0
2716 CompactRangeOptions compact_options;
2717 compact_options.change_level = true;
2718 compact_options.target_level = 0;
2719 Status s =
2720 db_->CompactRange(compact_options, GetCfHandle(), nullptr, nullptr);
2721 if (!s.ok()) {
2722 std::stringstream oss;
2723 oss << "Compaction failed: " << s.ToString();
2724 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(oss.str());
2725 return;
2726 }
2727
2728 // verify compaction result
2729 files_per_level = "";
2730 int num_files = 0;
2731 for (int i = 0; i < db_->NumberLevels(GetCfHandle()); i++) {
2732 db_->GetProperty(GetCfHandle(),
2733 "rocksdb.num-files-at-level" + std::to_string(i),
2734 &property);
2735
2736 // format print string
2737 char buf[100];
2738 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%s%s", (i ? "," : ""), property.c_str());
2739 files_per_level += buf;
2740
2741 num_files = atoi(property.c_str());
2742
2743 // level 0 should have only 1 file
2744 if (i == 0 && num_files != 1) {
2745 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
2746 "Number of db files at "
2747 "level 0 after compaction is " +
2748 std::to_string(num_files) + ", not 1.\n");
2749 return;
2750 }
2751 // other levels should have no file
2752 if (i > 0 && num_files != 0) {
2753 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
2754 "Number of db files at "
2755 "level " +
2756 std::to_string(i) + " after compaction is " +
2757 std::to_string(num_files) + ", not 0.\n");
2758 return;
2759 }
2760 }
2761
2762 fprintf(stdout, "files per level after compaction: %s\n",
2763 files_per_level.c_str());
2764}

2776class InMemoryHandler : public WriteBatch::Handler {
2777 public:
2778 InMemoryHandler(std::stringstream& row, bool print_values,
2779 bool write_after_commit,
2780 const std::map<uint32_t, const Comparator*>& ucmps)
2781 : Handler(),
2782 row_(row),
2783 print_values_(print_values),
2784 write_after_commit_(write_after_commit),
2785 ucmps_(ucmps) {}
2786
2787 void commonPutMerge(uint32_t cf, const Slice& key, const Slice& value) {
2788 std::string k = PrintKey(cf, key);
2789 if (print_values_) {
2790 std::string v = LDBCommand::StringToHex(value.ToString());
2791 row_ << k << " : ";
2792 row_ << v << " ";
2793 } else {
2794 row_ << k << " ";
2795 }
2796 }
2797
2798 Status PutCF(uint32_t cf, const Slice& key, const Slice& value) override {
2799 row_ << "PUT(" << cf << ") : ";
2800 commonPutMerge(cf, key, value);
2801 return Status::OK();
2802 }
2803
2804 Status PutEntityCF(uint32_t cf, const Slice& key,
2805 const Slice& value) override {
2806 row_ << "PUT_ENTITY(" << cf << ") : " << PrintKey(cf, key);
2807 if (print_values_) {
2808 row_ << " : ";
2809 const Status s =
2810 WideColumnsHelper::DumpSliceAsWideColumns(value, row_, true);
2811 if (!s.ok()) {
2812 return s;
2813 }
2814 }
2815
2816 row_ << ' ';
2817 return Status::OK();
2818 }
2819
2820 Status MergeCF(uint32_t cf, const Slice& key, const Slice& value) override {
2821 row_ << "MERGE(" << cf << ") : ";
2822 commonPutMerge(cf, key, value);
2823 return Status::OK();
2824 }
2825
2826 Status MarkNoop(bool) override {
2827 row_ << "NOOP ";
2828 return Status::OK();
2829 }
2830
2831 Status DeleteCF(uint32_t cf, const Slice& key) override {
2832 row_ << "DELETE(" << cf << ") : ";
2833 row_ << PrintKey(cf, key) << " ";
2834 return Status::OK();
2835 }
2836
2837 Status SingleDeleteCF(uint32_t cf, const Slice& key) override {
2838 row_ << "SINGLE_DELETE(" << cf << ") : ";
2839 row_ << PrintKey(cf, key) << " ";
2840 return Status::OK();
2841 }
2842
2843 Status DeleteRangeCF(uint32_t cf, const Slice& begin_key,
2844 const Slice& end_key) override {
2845 row_ << "DELETE_RANGE(" << cf << ") : ";
2846 row_ << PrintKey(cf, begin_key) << " ";
2847 row_ << PrintKey(cf, end_key) << " ";
2848 return Status::OK();
2849 }
2850
2851 Status MarkBeginPrepare(bool unprepare) override {
2852 row_ << "BEGIN_PREPARE(";
2853 row_ << (unprepare ? "true" : "false") << ") ";
2854 return Status::OK();
2855 }
2856
2857 Status MarkEndPrepare(const Slice& xid) override {
2858 row_ << "END_PREPARE(";
2859 row_ << LDBCommand::StringToHex(xid.ToString()) << ") ";
2860 return Status::OK();
2861 }
2862
2863 Status MarkRollback(const Slice& xid) override {
2864 row_ << "ROLLBACK(";
2865 row_ << LDBCommand::StringToHex(xid.ToString()) << ") ";
2866 return Status::OK();
2867 }
2868
2869 Status MarkCommit(const Slice& xid) override {
2870 row_ << "COMMIT(";
2871 row_ << LDBCommand::StringToHex(xid.ToString()) << ") ";
2872 return Status::OK();
2873 }
2874
2875 Status MarkCommitWithTimestamp(const Slice& xid,
2876 const Slice& commit_ts) override {
2877 row_ << "COMMIT_WITH_TIMESTAMP(";
2878 row_ << LDBCommand::StringToHex(xid.ToString()) << ", ";
2879 row_ << LDBCommand::StringToHex(commit_ts.ToString()) << ") ";
2880 return Status::OK();
2881 }
2882
2883 ~InMemoryHandler() override = default;
2884
2885 protected:
2886 Handler::OptionState WriteAfterCommit() const override {
2887 return write_after_commit_ ? Handler::OptionState::kEnabled
2888 : Handler::OptionState::kDisabled;
2889 }
2890
2891 private:
2892 std::string PrintKey(uint32_t cf, const Slice& key) {
2893 auto ucmp_iter = ucmps_.find(cf);
2894 if (ucmp_iter == ucmps_.end()) {
2895 // Fallback to default print slice as hex
2896 return LDBCommand::StringToHex(key.ToString());
2897 }
2898 size_t ts_sz = ucmp_iter->second->timestamp_size();
2899 if (ts_sz == 0) {
2900 return LDBCommand::StringToHex(key.ToString());
2901 } else {
2902 // This could happen if there is corruption or undetected comparator
2903 // change.
2904 if (key.size() < ts_sz) {
2905 return "CORRUPT KEY";
2906 }
2907 Slice user_key_without_ts = key;
2908 user_key_without_ts.remove_suffix(ts_sz);
2909 Slice ts = Slice(key.data() + key.size() - ts_sz, ts_sz);
2910 return LDBCommand::StringToHex(user_key_without_ts.ToString()) +
2911 "|timestamp:" + ucmp_iter->second->TimestampToString(ts);
2912 }
2913 }
2914 std::stringstream& row_;
2915 bool print_values_;
2916 bool write_after_commit_;
2917 const std::map<uint32_t, const Comparator*> ucmps_;
2918};
2919
2920void DumpWalFiles(Options options, const std::string& dir_or_file,
2921 bool print_header, bool print_values,
2922 bool only_print_seqno_gaps, bool is_write_committed,
2923 const std::map<uint32_t, const Comparator*>& ucmps,
2924 LDBCommandExecuteResult* exec_state) {
2925 std::vector<std::string> filenames;
2926 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::Env* env = options.env;
2927 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::Status st = env->GetChildren(dir_or_file, &filenames);
2928 std::optional<SequenceNumber> prev_batch_seqno;
2929 std::optional<uint32_t> prev_batch_count;
2930 if (!st.ok() || filenames.empty()) {
2931 // dir_or_file does not exist or does not contain children
2932 // Check its existence first
2933 Status s = env->FileExists(dir_or_file);
2934 // dir_or_file does not exist
2935 if (!s.ok()) {
2936 if (exec_state) {
2937 *exec_state = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
2938 dir_or_file + ": No such file or directory");
2939 }
2940 return;
2941 }
2942 // If it exists and doesn't have children, it should be a log file.
2943 if (dir_or_file.length() <= 4 ||
2944 dir_or_file.rfind(".log") != dir_or_file.length() - 4) {
2945 if (exec_state) {
2946 *exec_state = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
2947 dir_or_file + ": Invalid log file name");
2948 }
2949 return;
2950 }
2951 DumpWalFile(options, dir_or_file, print_header, print_values,
2952 only_print_seqno_gaps, is_write_committed, ucmps, exec_state,
2953 &prev_batch_seqno, &prev_batch_count);
2954 } else {
2955 WALFileIterator wal_file_iter(dir_or_file, filenames);
2956 if (!wal_file_iter.Valid()) {
2957 if (exec_state) {
2958 *exec_state = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
2959 dir_or_file + ": No valid wal logs found");
2960 }
2961 return;
2962 }
2963 std::string wal_file = wal_file_iter.GetNextWAL();
2964 while (!wal_file.empty()) {
2965 std::cout << "Checking wal file: " << wal_file << std::endl;
2966 DumpWalFile(options, wal_file, print_header, print_values,
2967 only_print_seqno_gaps, is_write_committed, ucmps, exec_state,
2968 &prev_batch_seqno, &prev_batch_count);
2969 if (exec_state->IsFailed() || !wal_file_iter.Valid()) {
2970 return;
2971 }
2972 wal_file = wal_file_iter.GetNextWAL();
2973 }
2974 }
2975}
2976
2977void DumpWalFile(Options options, const std::string& wal_file,
2978 bool print_header, bool print_values,
2979 bool only_print_seqno_gaps, bool is_write_committed,
2980 const std::map<uint32_t, const Comparator*>& ucmps,
2981 LDBCommandExecuteResult* exec_state,
2982 std::optional<SequenceNumber>* prev_batch_seqno,
2983 std::optional<uint32_t>* prev_batch_count) {
2984 const auto& fs = options.env->GetFileSystem();
2985 FileOptions soptions(options);
2986 std::unique_ptr<SequentialFileReader> wal_file_reader;
2987 Status status = SequentialFileReader::Create(
2988 fs, wal_file, soptions, &wal_file_reader, nullptr /* dbg */,
2989 nullptr /* rate_limiter */);
2990 if (!status.ok()) {
2991 if (exec_state) {
2992 *exec_state = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed("Failed to open WAL file " +
2993 status.ToString());
2994 } else {
2995 std::cerr << "Error: Failed to open WAL file " << status.ToString()
2996 << std::endl;
2997 }
2998 } else {
2999 StdErrReporter reporter;
3000 uint64_t log_number;
3001 FileType type;
3002
3003 // Comparators are available and will be used for formatting user key if DB
3004 // is opened for this dump wal operation.
3005 UnorderedMap<uint32_t, size_t> running_ts_sz;
3006 for (const auto& [cf_id, ucmp] : ucmps) {
3007 running_ts_sz.emplace(cf_id, ucmp->timestamp_size());
3008 }
3009 // we need the log number, but ParseFilename expects dbname/NNN.log.
3010 std::string sanitized = wal_file;
3011 size_t lastslash = sanitized.rfind('/');
3012 if (lastslash != std::string::npos) {
3013 sanitized = sanitized.substr(lastslash + 1);
3014 }
3015 if (!ParseFileName(sanitized, &log_number, &type)) {
3016 // bogus input, carry on as best we can
3017 log_number = 0;
3018 }
3019 log::Reader reader(options.info_log, std::move(wal_file_reader), &reporter,
3020 true /* checksum */, log_number);
3021 std::unordered_set<uint32_t> encountered_cf_ids;
3022 std::string scratch;
3023 WriteBatch batch;
3024 Slice record;
3025 std::stringstream row;
3026 if (print_header) {
3027 std::cout << "Sequence,Count,ByteSize,Physical Offset,Key(s)";
3028 if (print_values) {
3029 std::cout << " : value ";
3030 }
3031 std::cout << "\n";
3032 }
3033 while (status.ok() && reader.ReadRecord(&record, &scratch)) {
3034 row.str("");
3035 if (record.size() < WriteBatchInternal::kHeader) {
3036 reporter.Corruption(record.size(),
3037 Status::Corruption("log record too small"));
3038 } else {
3039 status = WriteBatchInternal::SetContents(&batch, record);
3040 if (!status.ok()) {
3041 std::stringstream oss;
3042 oss << "Parsing write batch failed: " << status.ToString();
3043 if (exec_state) {
3044 *exec_state = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(oss.str());
3045 } else {
3046 std::cerr << oss.str() << std::endl;
3047 }
3048 break;
3049 }
3050 const UnorderedMap<uint32_t, size_t> recorded_ts_sz =
3051 reader.GetRecordedTimestampSize();
3052 if (!running_ts_sz.empty()) {
3053 status = HandleWriteBatchTimestampSizeDifference(
3054 &batch, running_ts_sz, recorded_ts_sz,
3055 TimestampSizeConsistencyMode::kVerifyConsistency,
3056 /* seq_per_batch */ false, /* batch_per_txn */ true,
3057 /*new_batch=*/nullptr);
3058 if (!status.ok()) {
3059 std::stringstream oss;
3060 oss << "Format for user keys in WAL file is inconsistent with the "
3061 "comparator used to open the DB. Timestamp size recorded in "
3062 "WAL vs specified by "
3063 "comparator: {";
3064 bool first_cf = true;
3065 for (const auto& [cf_id, ts_sz] : running_ts_sz) {
3066 if (first_cf) {
3067 first_cf = false;
3068 } else {
3069 oss << ", ";
3070 }
3071 auto record_ts_iter = recorded_ts_sz.find(cf_id);
3072 size_t ts_sz_in_wal = (record_ts_iter == recorded_ts_sz.end())
3073 ? 0
3074 : record_ts_iter->second;
3075 oss << "(cf_id: " << cf_id << ", [recorded: " << ts_sz_in_wal
3076 << ", comparator: " << ts_sz << "])";
3077 }
3078 oss << "}";
3079 if (exec_state) {
3080 *exec_state = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(oss.str());
3081 } else {
3082 std::cerr << oss.str() << std::endl;
3083 }
3084 break;
3085 }
3086 }
3087 SequenceNumber sequence_number = WriteBatchInternal::Sequence(&batch);
3088 uint32_t batch_count = WriteBatchInternal::Count(&batch);
3089 assert(prev_batch_seqno);
3090 assert(prev_batch_count);
3091 assert(prev_batch_seqno->has_value() == prev_batch_count->has_value());
3092 // TODO(yuzhangyu): handle pessimistic transactions case.
3093 if (only_print_seqno_gaps) {
3094 if (!prev_batch_seqno->has_value() ||
3095 !prev_batch_count->has_value() ||
3096 prev_batch_seqno->value() + prev_batch_count->value() ==
3097 sequence_number) {
3098 *prev_batch_seqno = sequence_number;

3707 Status st = MaybePopulateReadTimestamp(cfh, scan_read_opts, &read_timestamp);
3708 if (!st.ok()) {
3709 std::stringstream oss;
3710 oss << "Scan failed: " << st.ToString();
3711 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(oss.str());
3712 return;
3713 }
3714 scan_read_opts.total_order_seek = true;
3715 Iterator* it = db_->NewIterator(scan_read_opts, cfh);
3716 if (start_key_specified_) {
3717 it->Seek(start_key_);
3718 } else {
3719 it->SeekToFirst();
3720 }
3721 int ttl_start;
3722 if (!ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_TTL_START, ttl_start, exec_state_)) {
3723 ttl_start = DBWithTTLImpl::kMinTimestamp; // TTL introduction time
3724 }
3725 int ttl_end;
3726 if (!ParseIntOption(option_map_, ARG_TTL_END, ttl_end, exec_state_)) {
3727 ttl_end = DBWithTTLImpl::kMaxTimestamp; // Max time allowed by TTL feature
3728 }
3729 if (ttl_end < ttl_start) {
3730 fprintf(stderr, "Error: End time can't be less than start time\n");
3731 delete it;
3732 return;
3733 }
3734 if (is_db_ttl_ && timestamp_) {
3735 fprintf(stdout, "Scanning key-values from %s to %s\n",
3736 TimeToHumanString(ttl_start).c_str(),
3737 TimeToHumanString(ttl_end).c_str());
3738 }
3739 for (;
3740 it->Valid() && (!end_key_specified_ || it->key().ToString() < end_key_);
3741 it->Next()) {
3742 if (is_db_ttl_) {
3743 TtlIterator* it_ttl = static_cast_with_check<TtlIterator>(it);
3744 int rawtime = it_ttl->ttl_timestamp();
3745 if (rawtime < ttl_start || rawtime >= ttl_end) {
3746 continue;
3747 }
3748 if (timestamp_) {
3749 fprintf(stdout, "%s ", TimeToHumanString(rawtime).c_str());
3750 }
3751 }
3752
3753 if (no_value_) {
3754 std::string key_str = it->key().ToString();
3755 if (is_key_hex_) {
3756 key_str = StringToHex(key_str);
3757 } else if (ldb_options_.key_formatter) {
3758 key_str = ldb_options_.key_formatter->Format(key_str);
3759 }
3760 fprintf(stdout, "%s\n", key_str.c_str());
3761 } else {
3762 std::string str =
3763 is_db_ttl_
3764 ? PrintKeyValue(it->key().ToString(),
3765 ts_sz == 0 ? "" : it->timestamp().ToString(),
3766 it->value().ToString(), is_key_hex_,
3767 is_value_hex_, ucmp)
3768 : PrintKeyValueOrWideColumns(
3769 it->key(), ts_sz == 0 ? "" : it->timestamp(), it->value(),
3770 it->columns(), is_key_hex_, is_value_hex_, ucmp);
3771 fprintf(stdout, "%s\n", str.c_str());
3772 }
3773
3774 if (get_write_unix_time_) {
3775 std::string write_unix_time;
3776 uint64_t write_time_int = std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max();
3777 Status s =
3778 it->GetProperty("rocksdb.iterator.write-time", &write_unix_time);
3779 if (s.ok()) {
3780 s = DecodeU64Ts(write_unix_time, &write_time_int);
3781 }
3782 if (!s.ok()) {
3783 fprintf(stdout, " Failed to get write unix time: %s\n",
3784 s.ToString().c_str());
3785 } else {
3786 fprintf(stdout, " write unix time: %s\n",
3787 std::to_string(write_time_int).c_str());
3788 }
3789 }
3790 num_keys_scanned++;
3791 if (max_keys_scanned_ >= 0 && num_keys_scanned >= max_keys_scanned_) {
3792 break;
3793 }
3794 }
3795 if (!it->status().ok()) { // Check for any errors found during the scan
3796 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(it->status().ToString());
3797 }
3798 delete it;
3799}
