4041const char* DBQuerierCommand::HELP_CMD = "help";
4042const char* DBQuerierCommand::GET_CMD = "get";
4043const char* DBQuerierCommand::PUT_CMD = "put";
4044const char* DBQuerierCommand::DELETE_CMD = "delete";
4045const char* DBQuerierCommand::COUNT_CMD = "count";
4046
4047DBQuerierCommand::DBQuerierCommand(
4048 const std::vector<std::string>& /*params*/,
4049 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& options,
4050 const std::vector<std::string>& flags)
4051 : LDBCommand(
4052 options, flags, false,
4053 BuildCmdLineOptions({ARG_TTL, ARG_HEX, ARG_KEY_HEX, ARG_VALUE_HEX})) {
4054
4055}
4056
4057void DBQuerierCommand::Help(std::string& ret) {
4058 ret.append(" ");
4059 ret.append(DBQuerierCommand::Name());
4060 ret.append(" [--" + ARG_TTL + "]");
4061 ret.append("\n");
4062 ret.append(
4063 " Starts a REPL shell. Type help for list of available "
4064 "commands.");
4065 ret.append("\n");
4066}
4067
4068void DBQuerierCommand::DoCommand() {
4069 if (!db_) {
4070 assert(GetExecuteState().IsFailed());
4071 return;
4072 }
4073
4074 std::string line;
4075 Status s;
4076 ColumnFamilyHandle* cfh = GetCfHandle();
4077 const Comparator* ucmp = cfh->GetComparator();
4078 while ((s.ok() || s.IsNotFound() || s.IsInvalidArgument()) &&
4079 getline(std::cin, line, '\n')) {
4080 std::string key;
4081 std::string timestamp;
4082 std::string value;
4083 // Reset to OK status before parsing and executing next user command.
4084 s = Status::OK();
4085 std::stringstream oss;
4086 // Parse line into std::vector<std::string>
4087 std::vector<std::string> tokens;
4088 ParsedParams parsed_params;
4089 size_t pos = 0;
4090 while (true) {
4091 size_t pos2 = line.find(' ', pos);
4092 std::string token =
4093 line.substr(pos, (pos2 == std::string::npos) ? pos2 : (pos2 - pos));
4094 ParseSingleParam(token, parsed_params, tokens);
4095 if (pos2 == std::string::npos) {
4096 break;
4097 }
4098 pos = pos2 + 1;
4099 }
4100
4101 if (tokens.empty() || !parsed_params.flags.empty()) {
4102 fprintf(stdout, "Bad command\n");
4103 continue;
4104 }
4105
4106 const std::string& cmd = tokens[0];
4107 ReadOptions read_options;
4108 WriteOptions write_options;
4109 Slice read_timestamp;
4110
4111 if (cmd == HELP_CMD) {
4112 fprintf(stdout,
4113 "get <key> [--read_timestamp=<uint64_ts>]\n"
4114 "put <key> [<write_timestamp>] <value>\n"
4115 "delete <key> [<write_timestamp>]\n"
4116 "count [--from=<start_key>] [--to=<end_key>] "
4117 "[--read_timestamp=<uint64_ts>]\n");
4118 } else if (cmd == DELETE_CMD && parsed_params.option_map.empty()) {
4119 key = (is_key_hex_ ? HexToString(tokens[1]) : tokens[1]);
4120 if (tokens.size() == 2) {
4121 s = db_->Delete(write_options, cfh, Slice(key));
4122 } else if (tokens.size() == 3) {
4123 Status encode_s = EncodeUserProvidedTimestamp(tokens[2], &timestamp);
4124 if (encode_s.ok()) {
4125 s = db_->Delete(write_options, cfh, Slice(key), Slice(timestamp));
4126 } else {
4127 fprintf(stdout, "delete gets invalid argument: %s\n",
4128 encode_s.ToString().c_str());
4129 continue;
4130 }
4131 } else {
4132 fprintf(stdout, "delete gets invalid arguments\n");
4133 continue;
4134 }
4135 oss << "delete " << (is_key_hex_ ? StringToHex(key) : key);
4136 if (!timestamp.empty()) {
4137 oss << " write_ts: " << ucmp->TimestampToString(timestamp);
4138 }
4139 if (s.ok()) {
4140 oss << " succeeded";
4141 } else {
4142 oss << " failed: " << s.ToString();
4143 }
4144 fprintf(stdout, "%s\n", oss.str().c_str());
4145 } else if (cmd == PUT_CMD && parsed_params.option_map.empty()) {
4146 key = (is_key_hex_ ? HexToString(tokens[1]) : tokens[1]);
4147 if (tokens.size() == 3) {
4148 value = (is_value_hex_ ? HexToString(tokens[2]) : tokens[2]);
4149 s = db_->Put(write_options, cfh, Slice(key), Slice(value));
4150 } else if (tokens.size() == 4) {
4151 value = (is_value_hex_ ? HexToString(tokens[3]) : tokens[3]);
4152 Status encode_s = EncodeUserProvidedTimestamp(tokens[2], &timestamp);
4153 if (encode_s.ok()) {
4154 s = db_->Put(write_options, cfh, Slice(key), Slice(timestamp),
4155 Slice(value));
4156 } else {
4157 fprintf(stdout, "put gets invalid argument: %s\n",
4158 encode_s.ToString().c_str());
4159 continue;
4160 }
4161 } else {
4162 fprintf(stdout, "put gets invalid arguments\n");
4163 continue;
4164 }
4165
4166 oss << "put " << (is_key_hex_ ? StringToHex(key) : key);
4167 if (!timestamp.empty()) {
4168 oss << " write_ts: " << ucmp->TimestampToString(timestamp);
4169 }
4170 oss << " => " << (is_value_hex_ ? StringToHex(value) : value);
4171 if (s.ok()) {
4172 oss << " succeeded";
4173 } else {
4174 oss << " failed: " << s.ToString();
4175 }
4176 fprintf(stdout, "%s\n", oss.str().c_str());
4177 } else if (cmd == GET_CMD && tokens.size() == 2) {
4178 key = (is_key_hex_ ? HexToString(tokens[1]) : tokens[1]);
4179 bool bad_option = false;
4180 for (auto& option : parsed_params.option_map) {
4181 if (option.first == "read_timestamp") {
4182 Status encode_s =
4183 EncodeUserProvidedTimestamp(option.second, &timestamp);
4184 if (!encode_s.ok()) {
4185 fprintf(stdout, "get gets invalid argument: %s\n",
4186 encode_s.ToString().c_str());
4187 bad_option = true;
4188 break;
4189 }
4190 read_timestamp = timestamp;
4191 read_options.timestamp = &read_timestamp;
4192 } else {
4193 fprintf(stdout, "get gets invalid arguments\n");
4194 bad_option = true;
4195 break;
4196 }
4197 }
4198 if (bad_option) {
4199 continue;
4200 }
4201 s = db_->Get(read_options, cfh, Slice(key), &value);
4202 if (s.ok()) {
4203 fprintf(stdout, "%s\n",
4204 PrintKeyValue(key, timestamp, value, is_key_hex_, is_value_hex_,
4205 ucmp)
4206 .c_str());
4207 } else {
4208 oss << "get " << (is_key_hex_ ? StringToHex(key) : key);
4209 if (!timestamp.empty()) {
4210 oss << " read_timestamp: " << ucmp->TimestampToString(timestamp);
4211 }
4212 oss << " status: " << s.ToString();
4213 fprintf(stdout, "%s\n", oss.str().c_str());
4214 }
4215 } else if (cmd == COUNT_CMD) {
4216 std::string start_key;
4217 std::string end_key;
4218 bool bad_option = false;
4219 for (auto& option : parsed_params.option_map) {
4220 if (option.first == "from") {
4221 start_key =
4222 (is_key_hex_ ? HexToString(option.second) : option.second);
4223 } else if (option.first == "to") {
4224 end_key = (is_key_hex_ ? HexToString(option.second) : option.second);
4225 } else if (option.first == "read_timestamp") {
4226 Status encode_s =
4227 EncodeUserProvidedTimestamp(option.second, &timestamp);
4228 if (!encode_s.ok()) {
4229 bad_option = true;
4230 fprintf(stdout, "count gets invalid argument: %s\n",
4231 encode_s.ToString().c_str());
4232 break;
4233 }
4234 read_timestamp = timestamp;
4235 read_options.timestamp = &read_timestamp;
4236 } else {
4237 fprintf(stdout, "count gets invalid arguments\n");
4238 bad_option = true;
4239 break;
4240 }
4241 }
4242 if (bad_option) {
4243 continue;
4244 }
4245
4246 Slice end_key_slice(end_key);
4247 uint64_t count = 0;
4248 if (!end_key.empty()) {
4249 read_options.iterate_upper_bound = &end_key_slice;
4250 }
4251 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> iter(db_->NewIterator(read_options, cfh));
4252 if (start_key.empty()) {
4253 iter->SeekToFirst();
4254 } else {
4255 iter->Seek(start_key);
4256 }
4257 while (iter->status().ok() && iter->Valid()) {
4258 count++;
4259 iter->Next();
4260 }
4261 if (iter->status().ok()) {
4262 fprintf(stdout, "%" PRIu64 "\n", count);
4263 } else {
4264 oss << "scan from "
4265 << (is_key_hex_ ? StringToHex(start_key) : start_key);
4266 if (!timestamp.empty()) {
4267 oss << " read_timestamp: " << ucmp->TimestampToString(timestamp);
4268 }
4269 oss << " to " << (is_key_hex_ ? StringToHex(end_key) : end_key)
4270 << " failed: " << iter->status().ToString();
4271 fprintf(stdout, "%s\n", oss.str().c_str());
4272 }
4273 } else {
4274 fprintf(stdout, "Unknown command %s\n", line.c_str());
4275 }
4276 }
4277 if (!(s.ok() || s.IsNotFound() || s.IsInvalidArgument())) {
4278 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(s.ToString());
4279 }
4280}

4387BackupEngineCommand::BackupEngineCommand(
4388 const std::vector<std::string>& /*params*/,
4389 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& options,
4390 const std::vector<std::string>& flags)
4391 : LDBCommand(options, flags, false /* is_read_only */,
4392 BuildCmdLineOptions({ARG_BACKUP_ENV_URI, ARG_BACKUP_FS_URI,
4393 ARG_BACKUP_DIR, ARG_NUM_THREADS,
4394 ARG_STDERR_LOG_LEVEL})),
4395 num_threads_(1) {
4396 auto itr = options.find(ARG_NUM_THREADS);
4397 if (itr != options.end()) {
4398 num_threads_ = std::stoi(itr->second);
4399 }
4400 itr = options.find(ARG_BACKUP_ENV_URI);
4401 if (itr != options.end()) {
4402 backup_env_uri_ = itr->second;
4403 }
4404 itr = options.find(ARG_BACKUP_FS_URI);
4405 if (itr != options.end()) {
4406 backup_fs_uri_ = itr->second;
4407 }
4408 if (!backup_env_uri_.empty() && !backup_fs_uri_.empty()) {
4409 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
4410 "you may not specity both --" + ARG_BACKUP_ENV_URI + " and --" +
4411 ARG_BACKUP_FS_URI);
4412 }
4413 itr = options.find(ARG_BACKUP_DIR);
4414 if (itr == options.end()) {
4415 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed("--" + ARG_BACKUP_DIR +
4416 ": missing backup directory");
4417 } else {
4418 backup_dir_ = itr->second;
4419 }
4420
4421 itr = options.find(ARG_STDERR_LOG_LEVEL);
4422 if (itr != options.end()) {
4423 int stderr_log_level = std::stoi(itr->second);
4424 if (stderr_log_level < 0 ||
4425 stderr_log_level >= InfoLogLevel::NUM_INFO_LOG_LEVELS) {
4426 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
4427 ARG_STDERR_LOG_LEVEL + " must be >= 0 and < " +
4428 std::to_string(InfoLogLevel::NUM_INFO_LOG_LEVELS) + ".");
4429 } else {
4430 logger_.reset(
4431 new StderrLogger(static_cast<InfoLogLevel>(stderr_log_level)));
4432 }
4433 }
4434}

4551void DumpSstFile(Options options, std::string filename, bool output_hex,
4552 bool show_properties, bool decode_blob_index,
4553 std::string from_key, std::string to_key) {
4554 if (filename.length() <= 4 ||
4555 filename.rfind(".sst") != filename.length() - 4) {
4556 std::cout << "Invalid sst file name." << std::endl;
4557 return;
4558 }
4559 // no verification
4560 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SstFileDumper dumper(
4561 options, filename, Temperature::kUnknown,
4562 2 * 1024 * 1024 /* readahead_size */,
4563 /* verify_checksum */ false, output_hex, decode_blob_index);
4564 Status st = dumper.ReadSequential(true, std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max(),
4565 !from_key.empty(), from_key,
4566 !to_key.empty(), to_key);
4567 if (!st.ok()) {
4568 std::cerr << "Error in reading SST file " << filename << st.ToString()
4569 << std::endl;
4570 return;
4571 }
4572
4573 if (show_properties) {
4574 const ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::TableProperties* table_properties;
4575
4576 std::shared_ptr<const ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::TableProperties>
4577 table_properties_from_reader;
4578 st = dumper.ReadTableProperties(&table_properties_from_reader);
4579 if (!st.ok()) {
4580 std::cerr << filename << ": " << st.ToString()
4581 << ". Try to use initial table properties" << std::endl;
4582 table_properties = dumper.GetInitTableProperties();
4583 } else {
4584 table_properties = table_properties_from_reader.get();
4585 }
4586 if (table_properties != nullptr) {
4587 std::cout << std::endl << "Table Properties:" << std::endl;
4588 std::cout << table_properties->ToString("\n") << std::endl;
4589 }
4590 }
4591}

4593void DumpBlobFile(const std::string& filename, bool is_key_hex,
4594 bool is_value_hex, bool dump_uncompressed_blobs) {
4595 using ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::blob_db::BlobDumpTool;
4596 BlobDumpTool tool;
4597 BlobDumpTool::DisplayType blob_type = is_value_hex
4598 ? BlobDumpTool::DisplayType::kHex
4599 : BlobDumpTool::DisplayType::kRaw;
4600 BlobDumpTool::DisplayType show_uncompressed_blob =
4601 dump_uncompressed_blobs ? blob_type : BlobDumpTool::DisplayType::kNone;
4602 BlobDumpTool::DisplayType show_blob =
4603 dump_uncompressed_blobs ? BlobDumpTool::DisplayType::kNone : blob_type;
4604
4605 BlobDumpTool::DisplayType show_key = is_key_hex
4606 ? BlobDumpTool::DisplayType::kHex
4607 : BlobDumpTool::DisplayType::kRaw;
4608 Status s = tool.Run(filename, show_key, show_blob, show_uncompressed_blob,
4609 /* show_summary */ true);
4610 if (!s.ok()) {
4611 fprintf(stderr, "Failed: %s\n", s.ToString().c_str());
4612 }
4613}

4682 std::cout << "Column family name: " << column_family.name << std::endl;

4694 std::cout << filename << " level:" << level.level << std::endl;
4695 std::cout << "------------------------------" << std::endl;
4696 DumpSstFile(options_, filename, false, true, decode_blob_index_);

4698 }
4699 }
4700 std::cout << "Blob Files" << std::endl;
4701 std::cout << "==============================" << std::endl;
4702 for (const BlobMetaData& blob_file : column_family.blob_files) {
4703 std::string filename =
4704 blob_file.blob_file_path + "/" + blob_file.blob_file_name;
4705 // Correct concatenation of filepath and filename:
4706 // Check that there is no double slashes (or more!) when concatenation

4709 std::cout << filename << std::endl;

4749DBLiveFilesMetadataDumperCommand::DBLiveFilesMetadataDumperCommand(

4761 ret.append(" [--" + ARG_SORT_BY_FILENAME + "] ");

4764
4765void DBLiveFilesMetadataDumperCommand::DoCommand() {
4766 if (!db_) {
4767 assert(GetExecuteState().IsFailed());
4768 return;
4769 }
4770 Status s;
4771
4772 std::vector<ColumnFamilyMetaData> metadata;
4773 db_->GetAllColumnFamilyMetaData(&metadata);
4774 if (sort_by_filename_) {
4775 std::cout << "Live SST and Blob Files:" << std::endl;
4776 // tuple of <file path, level, column family name>
4777 std::vector<std::tuple<std::string, int, std::string>> all_files;
4778
4779 for (const auto& column_metadata : metadata) {
4780 // Iterate Levels
4781 const auto& levels = column_metadata.levels;
4782 const std::string& cf = column_metadata.name;
4783 for (const auto& level_metadata : levels) {
4784 // Iterate SST files
4785 const auto& sst_files = level_metadata.files;
4786 int level = level_metadata.level;
4787 for (const auto& sst_metadata : sst_files) {
4788 // The SstFileMetaData.name always starts with "/",
4789 // however SstFileMetaData.db_path is the string provided by
4790 // the user as an input. Therefore we check if we can
4791 // concantenate the two strings directly or if we need to
4792 // drop a possible extra "/" at the end of SstFileMetaData.db_path.
4793 std::string filename =
4794 NormalizePath(sst_metadata.db_path + "/" + sst_metadata.name);
4795 all_files.emplace_back(filename, level, cf);
4796 } // End of for-loop over sst files
4797 } // End of for-loop over levels
4798
4799 const auto& blob_files = column_metadata.blob_files;
4800 for (const auto& blob_metadata : blob_files) {
4801 // The BlobMetaData.blob_file_name always starts with "/",
4802 // however BlobMetaData.blob_file_path is the string provided by
4803 // the user as an input. Therefore we check if we can
4804 // concantenate the two strings directly or if we need to
4805 // drop a possible extra "/" at the end of BlobMetaData.blob_file_path.
4806 std::string filename = NormalizePath(
4807 blob_metadata.blob_file_path + "/" + blob_metadata.blob_file_name);
4808 // Level for blob files is encoded as -1
4809 all_files.emplace_back(filename, -1, cf);
4810 } // End of for-loop over blob files
4811 } // End of for-loop over column metadata
4812
4813 // Sort by filename (i.e. first entry in tuple)
4814 std::sort(all_files.begin(), all_files.end());
4815
4816 for (const auto& item : all_files) {
4817 const std::string& filename = std::get<0>(item);
4818 int level = std::get<1>(item);
4819 const std::string& cf = std::get<2>(item);
4820 if (level == -1) { // Blob File
4821 std::cout << filename << ", column family '" << cf << "'" << std::endl;
4822 } else { // SST file
4823 std::cout << filename << " : level " << level << ", column family '"
4824 << cf << "'" << std::endl;
4825 }
4826 }
4827 } else {
4828 for (const auto& column_metadata : metadata) {
4829 std::cout << "===== Column Family: " << column_metadata.name
4830 << " =====" << std::endl;
4831
4832 std::cout << "Live SST Files:" << std::endl;
4833 // Iterate levels
4834 const auto& levels = column_metadata.levels;
4835 for (const auto& level_metadata : levels) {
4836 std::cout << "---------- level " << level_metadata.level
4837 << " ----------" << std::endl;
4838 // Iterate SST files
4839 const auto& sst_files = level_metadata.files;
4840 for (const auto& sst_metadata : sst_files) {
4841 // The SstFileMetaData.name always starts with "/",
4842 // however SstFileMetaData.db_path is the string provided by
4843 // the user as an input. Therefore we check if we can
4844 // concantenate the two strings directly or if we need to
4845 // drop a possible extra "/" at the end of SstFileMetaData.db_path.
4846 std::string filename =
4847 NormalizePath(sst_metadata.db_path + "/" + sst_metadata.name);
4848 std::cout << filename << std::endl;
4849 } // End of for-loop over sst files
4850 } // End of for-loop over levels
4851
4852 std::cout << "Live Blob Files:" << std::endl;
4853 const auto& blob_files = column_metadata.blob_files;
4854 for (const auto& blob_metadata : blob_files) {
4855 // The BlobMetaData.blob_file_name always starts with "/",
4856 // however BlobMetaData.blob_file_path is the string provided by
4857 // the user as an input. Therefore we check if we can
4858 // concantenate the two strings directly or if we need to
4859 // drop a possible extra "/" at the end of BlobMetaData.blob_file_path.
4860 std::string filename = NormalizePath(
4861 blob_metadata.blob_file_path + "/" + blob_metadata.blob_file_name);
4862 std::cout << filename << std::endl;
4863 } // End of for-loop over blob files
4864 } // End of for-loop over column metadata
4865 } // End of else ("not sort_by_filename")
4866 std::cout << "------------------------------" << std::endl;
4867}

4876WriteExternalSstFilesCommand::WriteExternalSstFilesCommand(

4894
4895void WriteExternalSstFilesCommand::DoCommand() {
4896 if (!db_) {
4897 assert(GetExecuteState().IsFailed());
4898 return;
4899 }
4900 ColumnFamilyHandle* cfh = GetCfHandle();
4901 SstFileWriter sst_file_writer(EnvOptions(), db_->GetOptions(), cfh);
4902 Status status = sst_file_writer.Open(output_sst_path_);
4903 if (!status.ok()) {
4904 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed("failed to open SST file: " +
4905 status.ToString());
4906 return;
4907 }
4908
4909 int bad_lines = 0;
4910 std::string line;
4911 std::ifstream ifs_stdin("/dev/stdin");
4912 std::istream* istream_p = ifs_stdin.is_open() ? &ifs_stdin : &std::cin;
4913 while (getline(*istream_p, line, '\n')) {
4914 std::string key;
4915 std::string value;
4916 if (ParseKeyValue(line, &key, &value, is_key_hex_, is_value_hex_)) {
4917 status = sst_file_writer.Put(key, value);
4918 if (!status.ok()) {
4919 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Failed(
4920 "failed to write record to file: " + status.ToString());
4921 return;
4922 }
4923 } else if (0 == line.find("Keys in range:")) {
4924 // ignore this line
4925 } else if (0 == line.find("Created bg thread 0x")) {

4927 } else {

4930 }

4937 }

4940 fprintf(stderr, "Warning: %d bad lines ignored.\n", bad_lines);
4941 }
4942 exec_state_ = LDBCommandExecuteResult::Succeed(
4943 "external SST file written to " + output_sst_path_);
